WEBVTT

00:07.877 --> 00:08.965
YOU'RE THINKING ABOUT
LIVING HERE NOW, AREN'T YOU?

00:09.009 --> 00:10.749
I'M JUST MOVING
NEXT DOOR.

00:10.793 --> 00:12.664
IS OLIVE
EVER GONNA COME HOME?

00:12.708 --> 00:13.926
SHE'S THE CLOSEST THING
TO A SISTER I HAVE.

00:13.970 --> 00:17.104
[ VOCALIZING ]

00:18.627 --> 00:20.063
Shh!

00:20.107 --> 00:21.804
WHAT IF I SLIP
AND TELL THE SECRET TO CHUCK?

00:21.847 --> 00:23.153
WHAT SECRET?

00:23.197 --> 00:25.112
I'M CHARLOTTE'S MOTHER.

00:25.155 --> 00:26.939
OH, MY GOD.
LILY IS CHUCK'S MOTHER.

00:26.983 --> 00:29.246
OHH!
THE WEIGHT HAS BEEN LIFTED!

00:29.290 --> 00:32.815
YOU WANT TO COME HOME?
MY WORK HERE IS DONE.

00:32.858 --> 00:34.164
COME ON, PIGBY.
[ SNORTS ]

00:34.208 --> 00:36.079
HMM.

00:36.123 --> 00:40.040
ARE YOU A PARENT
OR GUARDIAN, EMERSON COD?
I USED TO BE.

00:40.083 --> 00:41.998
YOU HAVE A DAUGHTER?
WHERE IS SHE?
WHY DON'T YOU EVER --

00:42.042 --> 00:45.393
UNH-UNH. UNH-UNH.
SCRATCHING AN ITCH
ONLY MAKES IT ITCHIER.

00:45.436 --> 00:47.699
I LOVE YOU, LIL' GUM SHOE.

00:56.752 --> 00:58.754
Narrator:
EMERSON COD WAS 5 MONTHS,

00:58.797 --> 01:00.973
3 DAYS, AND 4 HOURS OLD

01:01.017 --> 01:02.323
WHEN HIS MOTHER
PLANNED HIS DEATH.

01:02.366 --> 01:03.976
AH, BOO, BOO, BOO, BOO.

01:05.500 --> 01:07.545
Narrator:
IT WOULD BE QUICK, PAINLESS...

01:09.156 --> 01:10.331
AAAAAAH!

01:15.466 --> 01:16.728
[ SQUEAKS ]

01:16.772 --> 01:17.990
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

01:18.034 --> 01:19.253
Narrator:
...AND THE EASIEST WAY

01:19.296 --> 01:21.864
FOR PRIVATE DETECTIVE
CALISTA COD

01:21.907 --> 01:23.257
TO BUST A STOCK CLERK

01:23.300 --> 01:25.868
CLAIMING MILLIONS
IN PAIN AND SUFFERING

01:25.911 --> 01:28.871
AS THE RESULT
OF A FORKLIFT ACCIDENT.

01:28.914 --> 01:31.569
THE FIRM OF COD & COD
DEDICATED ITSELF

01:31.613 --> 01:34.529
TO THE PURSUIT OF TRUTH
AT ALL COSTS --

01:34.572 --> 01:38.054
A PURSUIT
YOUNG EMERSON FOUND "BADASS."

01:48.238 --> 01:50.022
[ WHIRRING ]

01:50.066 --> 01:53.504
FACED WITH SCOUNDRELS, CHEATS,
AND THE HAVOC THEY WREAKED,

01:53.548 --> 01:55.202
MOTHER AND SON MADE A VOW

01:55.245 --> 01:57.856
TO NEVER LET LIES
COME BETWEEN THEM.

01:57.900 --> 02:00.120
IT WAS A PROFITABLE DECISION
--

02:02.470 --> 02:07.170
THAT TRUTH IS THE CORNERSTONE
OF ANY SUCCESSFUL
RELATIONSHIP.

02:07.214 --> 02:09.694
YEARS LATER, PRIVATE
INVESTIGATOR EMERSON COD

02:09.738 --> 02:12.001
WAS LESS SUCCESSFUL
IN ANOTHER VENTURE --

02:12.044 --> 02:14.177
ASPIRING POP-UP-BOOK AUTHOR.

02:14.221 --> 02:15.744
"LIL' GUM SHOE" WAS BASED

02:15.787 --> 02:17.963
ON THE DETECTIVE'S
CHILDHOOD ADVENTURES.

02:18.007 --> 02:19.878
MORE IMPORTANTLY, IT WAS A MAP

02:19.922 --> 02:22.403
DESIGNED TO BRING HIS MISSING
DAUGHTER BACK TO HIM,

02:22.446 --> 02:24.709
IF ONLY HE COULD
GET IT PUBLISHED.

02:24.753 --> 02:28.278
"COMPLEX PLOT, LACK OF THEME,
CHILD ENDANGERMENT."

02:28.322 --> 02:29.932
MAN, THAT'S COLD.

02:29.975 --> 02:33.153
Narrator:
SO, AT THIS MOMENT,
EMERSON COD,

02:33.196 --> 02:35.938
A FAILURE
AT FATHERHOOD AND FICTION,

02:35.981 --> 02:37.722
DECIDED TO QUIT.

02:41.465 --> 02:43.032
Ned: WHO IS SHE?
I DON'T KNOW.

02:43.075 --> 02:46.253
SHE JUST ROLLED IN LIKE
A MOODY, MEAN THUNDERCLOUD.

02:46.296 --> 02:47.819
KNOW WHAT YOU WANT?

02:49.734 --> 02:52.346
YEAH -- NOTHIN'...

02:52.389 --> 02:53.782
WITH A SIDE
OF "BUZZ OFF."

02:53.825 --> 02:55.740
MA'AM, SORRY TO BOTHER.

02:55.784 --> 02:57.220
UM, PERHAPS
YOU DIDN'T REALIZE

02:57.264 --> 02:58.743
THIS IS
AN EATING ESTABLISHMENT --

02:58.787 --> 03:00.310
NOT A PARK BENCH,
FOR EXAMPLE,

03:00.354 --> 03:02.051
WHERE ONE
CAN LOITER AND SMOKE

03:02.094 --> 03:05.141
AND NOT CONSUME FOOD
TO ONE'S HEART'S CONTENT.

03:05.185 --> 03:07.491
GOT A PROBLEM?
WE CAN TAKE IT OUTSIDE.

03:10.625 --> 03:12.757
[ BELLS JINGLE ]

03:12.801 --> 03:14.933
OH, GOOD.
SOMEONE WITH A GUN.

03:14.977 --> 03:18.763
RHUBARB.
THE WHOLE PIE WILL DO.

03:18.807 --> 03:20.939
[ SNIFFS ]

03:20.983 --> 03:22.854
AND, MAMA...

03:22.898 --> 03:24.073
WHEN ARE YOU GONNA
TREAT YOURSELF

03:24.116 --> 03:25.509
AND SPRING
FOR A DECENT STOGIE?

03:25.553 --> 03:26.945
THE NEXT TIME I TRAIL

03:26.989 --> 03:28.947
A WHITE-COLLAR
MONEY LAUNDERER TO HAVANA.

03:28.991 --> 03:31.341
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

03:31.385 --> 03:33.561
MWAH!

03:33.604 --> 03:35.171
PEOPLE, I WANT TO
INTRODUCE YOU TO THE P.I.

03:35.215 --> 03:37.304
WHO TAUGHT ME
EVERYTHING I KNOW.

03:37.347 --> 03:39.306
SHE'S MY BEST BUD
AND MY MAMA, TO BOOT --

03:39.349 --> 03:40.611
CALISTA COD.

03:40.655 --> 03:43.135
I-I'M NED.
THIS IS CHUCK AND OLIVE.

03:43.179 --> 03:45.573
SO, CALISTA, WHAT BRINGS YOU
TO OUR NECK OF THE WOODS?

03:45.616 --> 03:48.924
FRAUD CASE, AND I'VE BEEN
MISSING MY LIL' GUM SHOE.

03:48.967 --> 03:50.752
NOW, CAN WE HIT A BAR?
I'M STARVING.

03:50.795 --> 03:52.667
Chuck: ISN'T SHE COMFORTING --
THE BRUTAL HONESTY,

03:52.710 --> 03:55.931
THE SARDONIC WIT,
AND THE APPETITE FOR HOOCH?

03:55.974 --> 03:58.542
I MEAN, ADD AN EYE PATCH,
AND CALISTA COULD BE LILY.

03:58.586 --> 04:00.849
HOW ARE YOU DOING
WITH THAT?
WHAT'S "THAT"?

04:00.892 --> 04:02.372
UH, LIVING WITH THE FACT

04:02.416 --> 04:03.808
THAT THE WOMAN
YOU'VE KNOWN YOUR WHOLE LIFE

04:03.852 --> 04:05.332
AS A TIED-FOR-FIRST-PLACE
FAVORITE AUNT

04:05.375 --> 04:06.724
IS REALLY YOUR MOTHER.

04:06.768 --> 04:08.639
OH, THAT "THAT."

04:08.683 --> 04:10.424
WELL, I'M HAPPY THAT I KNOW
I HAVE A MOTHER WHO'S ALIVE

04:10.467 --> 04:12.774
AND NOT SO HAPPY THAT
SHE CAN'T KNOW I'M ALIVE.

04:12.817 --> 04:15.733
OH, SUDDENLY WHAT WAS
COMFORTING IS GIVING WAY
TO SADNESS.

04:15.777 --> 04:17.692
THEN I'LL BE
YOUR COMFORTER.

04:17.735 --> 04:20.172
CONSIDER ME
YOUR KING-SIZED DUVET

04:20.216 --> 04:23.393
READY TO WRAP YOU IN
GOOSE-DOWN GOODNESS TONIGHT.

04:23.437 --> 04:26.353
I'D LOVE TO, BUT I'VE ALREADY
MADE PLANS WITH OLIVE.

04:26.396 --> 04:28.485
YOU TWO HAVE BEEN
HANGING OUT EVERY NIGHT
SINCE SHE GOT BACK --

04:28.529 --> 04:30.008
NOT THAT
I'VE BEEN COUNTING.

04:30.052 --> 04:31.923
ARE YOU NEW BEST FRIENDS
OR SOMETHING?

04:31.967 --> 04:34.230
NO. WAIT. I GUESS WE ARE.

04:34.274 --> 04:36.145
I HAVE A NEW BEST FRIEND.
ISN'T THAT SUPERB?

04:36.188 --> 04:37.929
Narrator: THE PIE MAKER
DID NOT THINK SO,

04:37.973 --> 04:40.845
FOR THE MORE TIME CHUCK SPENT
WITH HER NEW BEST FRIEND,

04:40.889 --> 04:42.282
THE LESS TIME SHE HAD FOR HIM.

04:42.325 --> 04:43.848
HE FELT ALONE,

04:43.892 --> 04:46.373
BUT HE FEARED THE TRUTH
WOULD MAKE HIM SOUND NEEDY,

04:46.416 --> 04:48.200
SO, INSTEAD, HE LIED.

04:48.244 --> 04:50.942
IT SURE IS SUPERB...
FOR YOU...

04:52.770 --> 04:53.945
...BOTH.

04:53.989 --> 04:55.643
WANT TO HEAD HOME, ROOMIE?
MM-HMM.

04:55.686 --> 04:57.471
Narrator: CHARLOTTE CHARLES'
AND OLIVE SNOOK'S

04:57.514 --> 05:00.300
DECISION TO COHABITATE
WAS SUDDEN,

05:00.343 --> 05:03.477
JUST LIKE OLIVE'S EARLIER
DECISION TO JOIN A NUNNERY,

05:03.520 --> 05:05.348
WHERE ALL
HER EARTHLY POSSESSIONS

05:05.392 --> 05:06.828
HAD BEEN GIVEN TO THE POOR.

05:06.871 --> 05:09.352
IT WAS A GESTURE
SHE HAD ALL BUT FORGOTTEN

05:09.396 --> 05:12.790
UNTIL SHE ARRIVED HOME
WITH A NEW PET PIG BY HER SIDE.

05:12.834 --> 05:14.531
Olive:
UH, IS THIS MY PLACE?

05:14.575 --> 05:16.316
I'M MOVING OUT
AFTER HAVING MOVED IN,

05:16.359 --> 05:18.100
WHICH CAME ORGANICALLY
FROM MISSING YOU

05:18.143 --> 05:20.537
AND WATERING YOUR PLANTS
LIKE YOU ASKED ME TO.

05:20.581 --> 05:24.149
DON'T WORRY. ALL THIS
WILL BE GONE BY TOMORROW.

05:24.193 --> 05:26.674
EVERYTHING?
I FIGURED YOU'D WANT TO
START FROM SCRATCH.

05:26.717 --> 05:29.067
Narrator:
TRUTHFULLY, OLIVE SNOOK DID NOT.

05:29.111 --> 05:31.635
WHAT SHE WANTED
WAS A FURNISHED APARTMENT.

05:31.679 --> 05:33.898
SCRATCH THAT.
LET'S BE ROOMMATES.

05:33.942 --> 05:35.422
OH, NO.
I-I COULDN'T IMPOSE.

05:35.465 --> 05:37.598
Narrator: TRUTHFULLY,
CHARLOTTE CHARLES COULD.

05:37.641 --> 05:39.948
LIKE OLIVE SNOOK,
SHE ENJOYED HER THINGS

05:39.991 --> 05:42.211
AND THE FEELING OF
INDEPENDENCE THEY BROUGHT HER.

05:42.254 --> 05:43.734
ALTHOUGH,
IF I WERE TO IMPOSE,

05:43.778 --> 05:45.127
YOU SHOULD KNOW THAT
I'M A MORNING SHOWERER,

05:45.170 --> 05:47.259
A HEAVY SLEEPER,
AND A DISH DRYER.

05:47.303 --> 05:50.480
AND I'M A LATE-NIGHT
BATH TAKER, A SNORER,
AND A DISH SCRUBBER.

05:50.524 --> 05:53.048
WELCOME HOME!
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:53.091 --> 05:54.745
IS THERE ANYTHING BIGGER
WE SHOULD DISCUSS?

05:54.789 --> 05:56.181
IF YOU'RE REFERRING
TO THE TIME YOU MADE ME

05:56.225 --> 05:58.358
AN UNWITTING DRUG MULE
FOR YOUR AUNTS --

05:58.401 --> 06:01.404
NO, I WASN'T.
GOOD, 'CAUSE I DONE ROASTED
THAT OLD CHESTNUT.

06:01.448 --> 06:03.406
AND I'M ALSO OKAY
THAT YOU HID THE FACT

06:03.450 --> 06:04.886
THAT ONE OF THOSE AUNTS
WERE REALLY MY MOTHER.

06:04.929 --> 06:06.844
RIGHT, JUST LIKE
I'M A-OKAY WITH THE FACT

06:06.888 --> 06:09.847
THAT YOU DIDN'T EXPLAIN TO ME
WHY YOU FAKED YOUR OWN DEATH.

06:09.891 --> 06:11.240
[ CHUCKLES ]
MY, LOOK AT ALL THOSE BRIDGES.

06:11.283 --> 06:14.548
AND ALL THAT WATER
FLOWING UNDER THEM.

06:14.591 --> 06:16.419
OH, I'M PROUD OF US --
WE'VE HAD THE COURAGE

06:16.463 --> 06:17.638
TO PUT IT ALL ON THE TABLE
AND DEAL WITH THE TOUGH STUFF.

06:17.681 --> 06:19.857
YEAH, AND JUST MOVE
RIGHT OFF OF IT.

06:19.901 --> 06:22.817
Narrator:
CHUCK AND OLIVE HAD
SIMULTANEOUS
AND SNEAKING SUSPICIONS

06:22.860 --> 06:24.993
THAT THEY WERE
FOOLING THEMSELVES.

06:25.036 --> 06:28.605
BUT THEY READ EACH OTHER'S
ANXIETY AS GIDDY EXCITEMENT,

06:28.649 --> 06:31.129
SO OLIVE SNOOK
CHANGED THE SUBJECT.

06:31.173 --> 06:33.131
BESIDES, WHO WOULD'VE THOUGHT
THEY WOULD HAVE EVER HIT IT OFF?

06:33.175 --> 06:35.220
WHICH REMINDS ME...

06:35.264 --> 06:37.919
WOULD YOU MIND IF I HAD
THE BED BY THE WINDOW?

06:37.962 --> 06:39.224
ABSOLUTELY...

06:39.790 --> 06:40.748
NOT.

06:40.791 --> 06:42.489
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

06:42.532 --> 06:45.056
[ CHUCKLING CONTINUES ]

06:45.100 --> 06:47.145
Calista: I KNEW I SHOULD'VE
KNITTED IT LARGER.

06:47.189 --> 06:48.408
WOOL STRETCHES.

06:48.451 --> 06:50.366
WELL, NOT TO CHINA,
SWEETHEART.

06:50.410 --> 06:52.194
HEY, HAVE YOU GOT
A GIRL SOMEWHERE?

06:52.237 --> 06:54.936
Narrator: EMERSON COD HAD LIED
TO HIS BEST FRIEND AND MOTHER

06:54.979 --> 06:56.459
ABOUT TWO THINGS --

06:56.503 --> 06:59.636
ONE, THAT HE DID HAVE
A GIRL SOMEWHERE, AGE 7.

06:59.680 --> 07:01.421
TWO, THAT HE HAD WRITTEN A
BOOK

07:01.464 --> 07:04.336
DESIGNED TO BRING THIS GIRL
BACK INTO HIS LIFE.

07:04.380 --> 07:06.034
WELL, SOMEBODY'S
BEEN FEEDING YOU.
WHAT'S HER NAME?

07:06.077 --> 07:08.253
PIE MAKER.
DAMN.

07:08.297 --> 07:11.387
AND DAMN SAD ME NOT
KNOWING MORE ABOUT WHAT'S
HAPPENING IN YOUR LIFE.

07:11.431 --> 07:13.433
I KNOW WE'RE BOTH BUSY,
BUT IT AIN'T RIGHT.

07:13.476 --> 07:15.173
Narrator:
EMERSON COD AGREED.

07:15.217 --> 07:17.480
IT WAS NO LONGER RIGHT
TO BE IN HIS MOTHER'S PRESENCE

07:17.524 --> 07:20.962
WITHOUT COMING CLEAN AND
CLEANING OFF THEIR
CORNERSTONE.

07:21.005 --> 07:24.618
HIS DECISION TO SHARE
HIS SECRETS WAS A NOBLE INTENT.

07:24.661 --> 07:25.575
ALRIGHT, MA,
HERE'S THE DILLY.

07:25.619 --> 07:28.360
[ DOOR OPENS ]

07:28.404 --> 07:31.363
[ Hispanic accent ]
MR. COD, I AM IN DESPERATE
NEED OF ASSISTANCE.

07:31.407 --> 07:33.757
WHAT MAKES YOU
SO DESPERATE, MISS...?

07:33.801 --> 07:36.630
VILLANUEVA.
VERONICA VILLANUEVA.

07:36.673 --> 07:38.501
AN UNSOLVED MURDER --

07:38.545 --> 07:40.285
NAMELY THAT
OF MY BEST FRIEND, JOE.

07:40.329 --> 07:42.244
OFFICE IS CLOSED.
FAMILY MATTER. SCRAM.

07:42.287 --> 07:44.464
PLEASE.
I AM OPENING MY HEART TO YOU.

07:44.507 --> 07:46.509
JUST OPEN THAT BLOUSE.

07:48.032 --> 07:51.732
YOU GOT A DESCRIPTION
OF THIS JOE?

07:51.775 --> 07:54.648
THEY FOUND HIS BODY DUMPED
IN AN ALLEYWAY LAST NIGHT.

07:54.691 --> 07:56.476
HE HAD BEEN MISSING
FOR TWO DAYS.

07:56.519 --> 07:58.869
JOE --
HE WAS LIKE A BROTHER.

07:58.913 --> 08:01.263
HE MEANT EVERYTHING TO ME.

08:01.306 --> 08:03.613
I WANT "YUSTICE"
AT ANY PRICE.

08:03.657 --> 08:06.398
THAT'S OUR KIND OF "YUSTICE."
WE'LL BE IN TOUCH.

08:08.357 --> 08:09.837
I'LL BE "DENTAL DAMNED."

08:09.880 --> 08:11.534
WITH A GIRL LIKE THAT,
YOU CERTAINLY SHOULD.

08:11.578 --> 08:13.580
I'M TALKING ABOUT A DENTIST

08:13.623 --> 08:16.060
BY THE NAME
OF DR. EUGENE HALIFAX --

08:16.104 --> 08:17.975
CAME TO SEE ME
THIS MORNING

08:18.019 --> 08:20.369
ABOUT THE MURDER
OF HIS BEST FRIEND, JOE.

08:20.412 --> 08:22.066
WITH MISS VILLANUEVA,

08:22.110 --> 08:24.504
HE'S A COSMO-DRINKING
SHOPAHOLIC.

08:25.330 --> 08:26.201
QUEER.

08:26.244 --> 08:27.289
YOU BET IT'S ODD.

08:27.332 --> 08:28.769
DR. EUGENE HAS JOE

08:28.812 --> 08:30.814
AS SOME TOUGH GUY
WHO'S TOUGH ON PLAQUE.

08:30.858 --> 08:33.164
SEEMS JOE WAS A DIFFERENT
FRIEND TO DIFFERENT PEOPLE.

08:33.208 --> 08:35.297
MEANING BOTH YOUR CLIENTS.
MM-HMM.

08:35.340 --> 08:36.820
GONNA THANK MAMA

08:36.864 --> 08:38.909
FOR GETTING YOU PAID TWICE
TO SOLVE ONE MURDER?

08:40.389 --> 08:41.608
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

08:44.567 --> 08:46.569
YEAH, THAT'S JOE,
ALRIGHT.

08:46.613 --> 08:48.092
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

08:48.136 --> 08:50.094
HEYA, FOLKS!
WHAT'S GOING ON?

08:50.138 --> 08:52.227
YOU'RE IN THE COUNTY MORGUE.
OUR CONDOLENCES.

08:52.270 --> 08:54.098
HAPPEN TO KNOW
HOW YOU HAPPENED IN HERE?

08:54.142 --> 08:56.231
LAST THING I REMEMBER,
I WAS GETTING READY TO PLAY BALL

08:56.274 --> 08:58.712
WHEN SUDDENLY THERE WAS
A DOOZY OF A PAIN IN MY BACK.

08:58.755 --> 08:59.974
STAB WOUND.

09:00.017 --> 09:01.802
KILLER STITCHED IT UP.
POORLY.

09:01.845 --> 09:02.933
LET ME SEE.

09:02.977 --> 09:04.021
OHH!
WHAT THE --

09:05.893 --> 09:07.068
OHH!

09:07.111 --> 09:09.897
OH, THANK YOU.
YOU'RE WELCOME.

09:09.940 --> 09:11.420
IS IT ME, OR IS THAT ODOR

09:11.463 --> 09:13.683
STRANGELY REMINISCENT
OF 8th-GRADE BIOLOGY?

09:13.727 --> 09:16.120
[ SNIFFS ]
SPECIFICALLY FORMALDEHYDE.

09:16.164 --> 09:18.296
THE CORONER MUST HAVE STARTED
EMBALMING ME ALREADY.

09:18.340 --> 09:20.864
CORONER DON'T EMBALM -- JUST
LOOKS FOR THE CAUSE OF DEATH.

09:20.908 --> 09:22.649
PRESERVING HAPPENS
AFTER AND ELSEWHERE.

09:22.692 --> 09:24.476
AH-CHOO!
BLESS YOU.

09:24.520 --> 09:27.392
NO. BLESS DOWNY.
SHE WAS MY ONE-AND-ONLY.

09:27.436 --> 09:29.177
I NEVER GOT A CHANCE
TO TELL HER HOW MUCH I CARED.

09:29.220 --> 09:31.048
NOW SHE'LL NEVER KNOW.

09:31.092 --> 09:33.442
ANY IDEA WHO'D WANT TO
PICKLE YOUR GHERKIN? NONE.

09:33.485 --> 09:35.575
I WONDER IF THIS HAS ANYTHING
TO DO WITH MY BEST FRIEND.

09:35.618 --> 09:37.272
WHICH ONE?
VERONICA OR DR. EUGENE?

09:37.315 --> 09:39.970
YOU KNOW THOSE TWO?
SMALL WORLD.

09:40.014 --> 09:43.321
PROMISE YOU'LL KEEP
AN EYE ON THEM FOR ME?
WE PLAN TO.

09:43.365 --> 09:46.586
LOOKS LIKE WE GOT TO
GET FRIENDLY WITH A
COUPLE OF BEST FRIENDS.

09:46.629 --> 09:47.804
OH!

09:51.982 --> 09:53.593
Narrator:
UNDER NORMAL CIRCUMSTANCES,

09:53.636 --> 09:55.856
A P.I. WOULD QUESTION
SEPARATE CLIENTS SEPARATELY.

09:55.899 --> 09:59.468
HOWEVER, THE PRESENCE
OF ONE P.I.'s P.I. MOTHER

09:59.511 --> 10:00.817
ALLOWED HIM TO EMPLOY

10:00.861 --> 10:03.080
A TIME-SAVING
INTERROGATION TECHNIQUE

10:03.124 --> 10:05.387
KNOWN AS THE "KALASHNI-COD."

10:05.430 --> 10:08.085
LIKE THE RUSSIAN MACHINE GUN
FOR WHICH IT WAS NAMED,

10:08.129 --> 10:10.044
ITS OPERATION WAS SIMPLE.

10:10.087 --> 10:12.612
THE SCOPE WAS SET,
THE MAGAZINE LOADED,

10:12.655 --> 10:14.352
AND THE TRIGGER PULLED.
[ HANDS SLAP TABLE ]

10:14.396 --> 10:16.137
WHO'S JOE'S BEST FRIEND?
WHO'S JOE'S BEST FRIEND?

10:16.180 --> 10:18.443
I GOT IT ON GOOD AUTHORITY
JOE'S B.F.F. MADE HIM R.I.P.

10:18.487 --> 10:19.836
WHO WANTS THE TITLE NOW?

10:19.880 --> 10:21.664
WHERE WERE YOU LAST FRIDAY?
WHERE WERE YOU?

10:21.708 --> 10:23.753
WERE YOU OBSESSED?
WHERE'D YOU BUY
THE FORMALDEHYDE?

10:23.797 --> 10:25.668
DID GIVING HIM THE STAB-STAB
MAKE YOU FEEL GOOD?

10:25.712 --> 10:27.148
I'M NO SUSPECT.
I HIRED YOU.

10:27.191 --> 10:28.976
I THINK I'D LIKE
MY MONEY BACK.

10:29.019 --> 10:31.674
I DON'T GIVE NO DAMN REFUNDS
TO PEOPLE WHO WASTE MY TIME.

10:31.718 --> 10:33.067
WHEN YOU RETAIN MY SERVICES,

10:33.110 --> 10:35.069
I EXPECT THE FACTS,
AND I MEAN ALL OF THEM.

10:35.112 --> 10:36.940
BUT LOOKING AT YOU TWO
WITH YOUR AVERTED EYES...

10:36.984 --> 10:38.507
...LOWERED HEADS...
...AND NIBBLED LIPS

10:38.550 --> 10:40.161
MAKES ME THINK
YOU HIDING SOMETHING.

10:40.204 --> 10:41.510
[ HANDS SLAP TABLE ]
WHAT IS IT?
WHAT IS IT?

10:41.553 --> 10:44.121
FINE,
I'LL TELL YOU THE TRUTH --

10:44.165 --> 10:47.298
THE DIRTY,
HUMILIATING TRUTH.

10:47.342 --> 10:48.735
JOE WAS A FRESCORT.

10:48.778 --> 10:51.520
IT'S SHORT
FOR "FRIEND/ESCORT,"

10:51.563 --> 10:52.521
BASICALLY
A FRIEND FOR HIRE.

10:52.564 --> 10:53.870
YOU PICK FROM THE CATALOG.

10:53.914 --> 10:55.872
THEY BECOME ANYONE
YOU WANT THEM TO BE.

10:55.916 --> 10:58.440
WHAT'S WRONG WITH PICKING
SOMEBODY THE OLD-FASHIONED WAY,

10:58.483 --> 11:01.269
WALKING UP TO THEM AND SAYING,
"HI, MY NAME IS BLAH-DEE-BLAH.

11:01.312 --> 11:04.228
DO YOU LIKE BLOO-DEE-BLOOIN'?
ME TOO. LET'S BE FRIENDS"?

11:04.272 --> 11:05.665
BUT I'M SHY.

11:05.708 --> 11:08.015
I GET WHY DR. BASHFUL
NEEDS A PAY-A-PAL.

11:08.058 --> 11:09.494
BUT BACK WHEN I HAD A RACK

11:09.538 --> 11:11.714
AND A COUPLE OF GETAWAY STICKS
LIKE YOURS,

11:11.758 --> 11:14.282
I HAD NO TROUBLE
MAKING ACQUAINTANCES.

11:14.325 --> 11:16.632
THIS...

11:16.676 --> 11:18.460
ATTRACTS ALL KINDS.

11:18.503 --> 11:20.375
BUT NO ONE WANTS
TO KNOW WHO I AM.

11:20.418 --> 11:23.683
MEN ONLY SEE ME
AS A SCORE NOT YET SCORED.

11:23.726 --> 11:24.727
AND THE WOMEN?

11:24.771 --> 11:26.468
THIS...
YEAH, WE GOT IT.

11:26.511 --> 11:28.513
IT PROMOTES
INSTANT JEALOUSY.

11:28.557 --> 11:29.863
I WAS ALL ALONE,

11:29.906 --> 11:32.300
SO I CALLED IN
THE PROFESSIONALS.

11:32.343 --> 11:34.389
Narrator:
AS EMERSON COD READ THE WORDS,

11:34.432 --> 11:37.740
HE WAS REMINDED
OF FRESCORT JOE'S FINAL ONES --

11:37.784 --> 11:40.830
THAT HIS MURDER
MAY HAVE HAD TO DO WITH...

11:40.874 --> 11:43.659
"MY BEST FRIEND, INC."?

11:43.703 --> 11:44.878
ALRIGHT, EVERYBODY
KNOW WHAT THEIR JOB IS?

11:44.921 --> 11:47.010
OLIVE AND I ARE
FRESCORT WANNABES.

11:47.054 --> 11:49.404
OUR MISSION -- TO FIND
JOE'S ONE-AND-ONLY, DOWNY.
ALRIGHT, GOOD.

11:49.447 --> 11:51.275
MEANWHILE,
ME AND THE PIE MAN ARE GONNA

11:51.319 --> 11:53.756
HAVE A SIT-DOWN CHITTY-CHAT
WITH THE C.E.O. OF THE COMPANY,

11:53.800 --> 11:56.150
SEE WHO JOE WAS PRETEND-
FRIENDING THE NIGHT HE DIED.

11:56.193 --> 11:58.718
ANY QUESTIONS?

11:58.761 --> 12:00.589
THAT WAS RHETORICAL.
MY QUERY IS NOT.

12:00.632 --> 12:02.504
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU AND YOUR
MOM WORKING THIS TOGETHER?

12:02.547 --> 12:04.636
SHE'S WORKING ON HER OWN CASE,
AND I MIGHT NEED A DIVERSION,

12:04.680 --> 12:07.291
SO, AS I SAID,
YOU WITH ME.

12:07.335 --> 12:08.858
THIS ISN'T A QUESTION,
MORE OF A SUGGESTION --

12:08.902 --> 12:10.338
MERELY A TINY CHANGE
OF PLAN,

12:10.381 --> 12:11.992
WHERE CHUCK GOES UNDERCOVER

12:12.035 --> 12:15.343
WITH ME, FOR INSTANCE.

12:15.386 --> 12:18.694
Narrator: THE PIE MAKER'S
INTENTION WASN'T TO MAKE WAVES.

12:18.738 --> 12:23.046
HE WAS JUST TRYING TO SPEND TIME
WITH HIS BELOVED CHUCK.

12:23.090 --> 12:24.482
UH, YEAH, SURE.

12:24.526 --> 12:25.875
IT'S JUST THAT
OLIVE AND I HAD KIND OF

12:25.919 --> 12:28.051
COME UP WITH
BACKSTORIES AND ALIASES.

12:28.095 --> 12:30.271
AND A SECRET
INCOGNITO-PARTNERS HANDSHAKE.

12:30.314 --> 12:32.360
YEAH.

12:32.403 --> 12:33.274
[ FINGERS SNAP ]

12:33.317 --> 12:35.145
YEAH, THAT'S NICE.

12:35.189 --> 12:37.234
PLAN STAYS AS PLANNED.
MOVE OUT.

12:41.195 --> 12:42.762
WELCOME TO MY BEST FRIEND,

12:42.805 --> 12:44.633
WHERE EVERYONE'S
IN THE IN-CROWD.

12:44.676 --> 12:47.592
I'M A P.I. --
LESS INTERESTED IN THE
IN-CROWD

12:47.636 --> 12:49.464
AND MORE IN THE "OUT,"
AS IN MURDER.

12:49.507 --> 12:52.510
YOU'RE HERE ABOUT JOE.
SUCH A DEVASTATING LOSS.

12:52.554 --> 12:54.208
HE WAS OUR TOP PERFORMER.

12:54.251 --> 12:56.645
THAT'S WHAT YOU PEDDLE
AROUND HERE -- PERFORMERS?

12:56.688 --> 12:59.213
TRUTHFULLY,
I'D SAY IT'S ATONEMENT.

12:59.256 --> 13:01.911
BACK IN HIGH SCHOOL,
I WAS A COLOSSAL CREEP.

13:01.955 --> 13:04.435
MATH GEEKS,
MALE CHEERLEADERS...

13:04.479 --> 13:07.090
EVEN THE PITIFUL
TEAM MASCOT

13:07.134 --> 13:09.266
WERE JUST
SAD, PIMPLY TARGETS

13:09.310 --> 13:13.053
FOR A VARSITY QUARTERBACK
LIKE MYSELF...

13:13.096 --> 13:15.838
UNTIL TWO BLITZING LINEBACKERS
DESTROYED MY KNEE.

13:15.882 --> 13:17.274
SUDDENLY I WAS NO DIFFERENT

13:17.318 --> 13:19.711
FROM ALL THOSE NERDS
I PUT THROUGH HELL.

13:20.887 --> 13:22.279
FROM THAT POINT ON,

13:22.323 --> 13:24.978
I SWORE
I'D USE MY POWERS FOR GOOD,

13:25.021 --> 13:27.894
PROVIDING PEOPLE,
FOR A NOMINAL FEE,

13:27.937 --> 13:31.071
WITH WHAT EVERYONE DESERVES --

13:31.114 --> 13:32.246
FRIENDSHIP.

13:32.289 --> 13:33.638
WELL, JUDGING
BY THESE DIGS,

13:33.682 --> 13:35.466
YOUR NOMINAL FEES
HAVE BEEN ADDING UP.

13:35.510 --> 13:37.251
NO MATTER
WHAT THE MODERN WORLD SAYS

13:37.294 --> 13:39.949
ABOUT GADGETRY BRINGING US
CLOSER TOGETHER,

13:39.993 --> 13:42.212
IT'S DRIVEN US
FURTHER APART.

13:42.256 --> 13:44.649
WE'RE ISOLATED, ALL ALONE.

13:44.693 --> 13:47.000
BUT ONCE TRAINED,
MY FRESCORTS FUNCTION

13:47.043 --> 13:49.002
AS THE BEST COMPANIONS
MONEY CAN BUY.

13:49.045 --> 13:51.178
WHO WAS JOE COMPANIONING
THE NIGHT HE DIED?

13:52.309 --> 13:53.876
NO CLIENT APPOINTMENTS.

13:53.920 --> 13:55.312
MIND IF I TAKE A GANDER?

13:55.356 --> 13:57.184
WE KEEP ALL OF OUR RECORDS
CONFIDENTIAL.

13:57.227 --> 14:00.709
AH, THE HUG MACHINE.
OUR MOST VALUABLE TEACHING TOOL.

14:00.752 --> 14:02.493
HOW ABOUT A DEMONSTRATION
ON MY ASSOCIATE?

14:02.537 --> 14:04.017
NO, THANK YOU.
Divert.

14:04.060 --> 14:07.150
COME ON, YOU!
[ CHUCKLES ]

14:07.194 --> 14:09.761
SEE, PROPER HUGS
ARE A SCIENCE.

14:09.805 --> 14:13.417
THEY MUST BE PLATONIC
BUT NOT COLD,

14:13.461 --> 14:16.812
FIRM BUT NOT PAINFUL.

14:16.856 --> 14:19.293
Narrator: THE PIE MAKER DIDN'T
WANT TO BE HUGGED BY A MACHINE.

14:19.336 --> 14:22.644
HE WANTED TO BE HUGGED
BY THE ONE HE WAS LONELY FOR.

14:26.474 --> 14:27.867
BUT FOR A FLEETING MOMENT,

14:27.910 --> 14:30.260
THE PIE MAKER'S ALONENESS
ABATED,

14:30.304 --> 14:32.175
SO HE CLOSED HIS EYES,

14:32.219 --> 14:34.090
THOUGHT OF CHUCK,
AND HUGGED BACK.

14:34.134 --> 14:35.831
I LIKE THAT.

14:35.875 --> 14:38.486
WE'LL HAVE THE MODELS IN
THE GIFT SHOP FOR CHRISTMAS.

14:38.529 --> 14:41.228
I'LL MAKE SURE THERE'S ONE
IN YOUR STOCKING. COME ON.

14:41.271 --> 14:44.361
Narrator: EMERSON COD
HAD UNCOVERED JOE'S HOME ADDRESS

14:44.405 --> 14:47.538
AS CHUCK AND OLIVE
ADDRESSED GOING UNDERCOVER.

14:47.582 --> 14:49.801
UH, BARB? UM, HI.

14:49.845 --> 14:52.761
MY NAME IS KITTY PIMMS,
AND THIS IS PATTY BOOTS.

14:52.804 --> 14:54.502
WE'RE TWO HIGHLY MOTIVATED
CANDIDATES

14:54.545 --> 14:56.417
READY TO BEFRIEND
THE SAD AND LONELY.

14:56.460 --> 14:57.461
FOR PAY.

14:57.505 --> 14:59.768
j& KITTY PIMMS, PATTY BOOTS j&

14:59.811 --> 15:01.726
WHAT WONDERFULLY
RHYTHMIC NAMES.

15:01.770 --> 15:03.772
THEY JUST SCREAM "GOOD HUMOR"
AND "BON HOMIE"!

15:03.815 --> 15:07.471
NOW, CAN YOU
F-F-FAKE IT REAL?

15:07.515 --> 15:09.082
W-W-W-W-WHAT?

15:09.125 --> 15:10.910
W-W-WERE YOU MAKING FUN
OF MY STUTTERING?

15:10.953 --> 15:12.085
NO, I WAS JUST --

15:12.128 --> 15:13.782
I DON'T STUTTER,
BUT IF I DID,

15:13.825 --> 15:16.219
WHAT YOU DID WOULD SUBTLY
PUT ME AT EASE BY SAYING,

15:16.263 --> 15:20.571
"HEY, YOU'RE OKAY.
I'M OKAY. WE'RE OKAY."

15:20.615 --> 15:21.659
MM-KAY?

15:21.703 --> 15:23.444
NOW, BACK TO "FAKE IT REAL."

15:23.487 --> 15:26.099
ON ANY GIVEN DAY,
CLIENTS ARE GONNA DEPEND ON YOU

15:26.142 --> 15:28.666
TO SUMMON UP
EVERY FEELING IN THE BOOK

15:28.710 --> 15:31.104
EVEN IF
YOU'RE NOT FEELING IT.

15:31.147 --> 15:32.932
SHOW ME HAPPY.

15:32.975 --> 15:33.976
SAD.

15:34.020 --> 15:35.108
SURPRISE.

15:35.151 --> 15:37.806
CONSTERNATION.
CONSTIPATION.

15:37.849 --> 15:39.416
YOU KNOW WHAT
I'M SHOWING YOU?

15:39.460 --> 15:42.550
HECK, YEAH! WE ARE GETTING YOU
INTO TRAINING ASAP!

15:42.593 --> 15:44.291
WHOO!

15:44.334 --> 15:47.120
EXCEPT I HEARD THIS JOB
CAN BE KIND OF DANGEROUS.

15:47.163 --> 15:48.599
YOU ARE REFERRING
TO JOE.

15:48.643 --> 15:50.079
IT'S SO HORRIBLE.

15:50.123 --> 15:51.689
D-DID YOU KNOW HIM?

15:51.733 --> 15:55.215
JUST BY NAME. FRESCORTS
ARE FORBIDDEN TO FRATERNIZE.

15:55.258 --> 15:56.520
YOU TWO ARE FRIENDS,
AREN'T YOU?

15:56.564 --> 15:58.827
UH. DON'T ANSWER.
I CAN TELL.

15:58.870 --> 16:00.263
THING IS, YOU'RE AWESOME,

16:00.307 --> 16:01.786
AND I ONLY WANT
TO BRING THE BEST PEOPLE

16:01.830 --> 16:04.224
INTO THIS ORGANIZATION, SO...

16:04.267 --> 16:05.877
[ KNOCKING ON DESK ]

16:05.921 --> 16:08.184
We'll just keep things
on the QT, okay? Shh.

16:08.228 --> 16:09.881
WE WON'T EVEN CARPOOL.

16:09.925 --> 16:12.449
Narrator: AT THAT MOMENT,
ANOTHER CARPOOL HAD LANDED

16:12.493 --> 16:14.190
AT THE APARTMENT
OF A MURDER VICTIM.

16:14.234 --> 16:15.844
THEM FRESCORTS
AIN'T NOTHING

16:15.887 --> 16:18.934
BUT A BUNCH OF CONS
HIDING BEHIND GOOD INTENTIONS.

16:18.978 --> 16:20.457
MY EXPERIENCE --

16:20.501 --> 16:22.720
PEOPLE DON'T APPRECIATE
BEING CONNED,

16:22.764 --> 16:24.113
EVEN WHEN
THEY'RE PATHETIC LOSERS

16:24.157 --> 16:26.376
WHO SIGNED UP FOR IT
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

16:26.420 --> 16:28.726
WE'RE GONNA GO IN JOE'S PLACE
AND FIND THAT LIST,

16:28.770 --> 16:31.425
SEE WHICH ONE OF HIS CLIENTS
DID HIM IN.

16:31.468 --> 16:34.558
WHY ARE THEY PATHETIC LOSERS?
'CAUSE THEY'RE ALONE?

16:34.602 --> 16:36.560
BECAUSE THEY'RE PAYING
FOR SOMETHING THAT'S FREE.

16:36.604 --> 16:38.910
THERE'S NOTHING WRONG WITH
NEEDING A LITTLE EXTRA HELP.

16:38.954 --> 16:40.390
NO ONE THINKS TWICE
IF A PERSON

16:40.434 --> 16:41.826
WITH A WOBBLY BACKHAND
HIRES A TENNIS COACH.

16:41.870 --> 16:43.089
AND I'M GUESSING
YOU HAVE NO CLUE

16:43.132 --> 16:44.742
HOW TO BAKE
A RHUBARB CUSTARD PIE.

16:44.786 --> 16:47.093
BUT DO I CALL YOU PATHETIC
FOR PAYING ME TO DO IT?

16:47.136 --> 16:48.877
YOU'VE HAD A BEST FRIEND
SINCE BIRTH.

16:48.920 --> 16:50.835
NOT ALL OF US
HAVE BEEN THAT LUCKY.

16:50.879 --> 16:53.490
YEAH, WELL, DON'T BE
TOO JEALOUS OF MY LUCK.

16:53.534 --> 16:55.927
AIN'T BUT ONE SORRY LEAF
HANGING OFF THAT CLOVER.

16:55.971 --> 16:58.800
YOU KNOW, MOM AND ME
AIN'T SUPPOSED TO HAVE
NO LIES BETWEEN US.

16:58.843 --> 17:00.280
WELL, TECHNICALLY,
I NEVER LIED,

17:00.323 --> 17:02.195
BUT I ALSO NEVER TOLD HER
I HAVE A DAUGHTER.

17:02.238 --> 17:04.110
MOST MOTHERS WOULD CONSIDER THAT
SPLITTING HAIRS.

17:04.153 --> 17:06.982
SHE SPENT HER WHOLE LIFE
TEACHING ME HOW TO COLLAR CONS.

17:08.636 --> 17:10.725
I GUESS I'M JUST EMBARRASSED
TO HAVE HER KNOW

17:10.768 --> 17:12.857
THAT MY EX CONNED ME.

17:12.901 --> 17:14.163
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT?

17:14.207 --> 17:16.774
I'M CHUCKING MY CHAGRIN
OVERBOARD.

17:16.818 --> 17:18.733
I'M LETTING LOOSE
THE TRUTH.

17:18.776 --> 17:20.648
YEP.

17:20.691 --> 17:22.693
I'M GONNA SIT MAMA DOWN...

17:24.347 --> 17:25.522
TAKE A DEEP BREATH...

17:25.566 --> 17:27.524
AND LOOK HER
STRAIGHT IN THE --

17:35.315 --> 17:36.446
Randy:
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

17:36.490 --> 17:38.883
CAT GOT YOUR EYE?
[ LAUGHS ]

17:38.927 --> 17:41.103
SORRY. IT'S JUST GLASS.

17:41.147 --> 17:43.453
YEAH, IT'S FOR A SCULPTURE
T-THAT I'M WORKING ON.

17:43.497 --> 17:45.847
WE'RE PRIVATE INVESTIGATORS
LOOKING INTO A MURDER.

17:47.936 --> 17:49.068
JOE WAS MY ROOMMATE.

17:49.111 --> 17:50.286
MM-HMM.

17:50.330 --> 17:52.332
WHAT'S YOUR NAME,
ROOMMATE?

17:52.375 --> 17:54.073
RANDY MANN.
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:54.116 --> 17:56.727
I GOT SOME KNEE-SLAPPERS
ABOUT THAT. YOU WANT TO HEAR?

17:56.771 --> 17:58.294
UH...

17:58.338 --> 18:00.557
IN THE FACE OF TRAGEDY,
I TRY TO KEEP THINGS LIGHT.

18:00.601 --> 18:04.083
IT'S JUST WEIRD
NOT HAVING HIM AROUND ANYMORE.

18:04.126 --> 18:05.562
JOE HAD
SUCH A BIG PERSONALITY.

18:05.606 --> 18:07.651
IT'S TOUGH -- YOU SHARE
YOUR LIFE WITH SOMEONE,

18:07.695 --> 18:10.306
AND SUDDENLY THERE'S
AN ABYSS WHERE A PERSON
ALWAYS WAS BEFORE.

18:10.350 --> 18:11.481
YOU LOST A ROOMMATE, TOO?

18:11.525 --> 18:12.961
AND GIRLFRIEND.
SAME PERSON.

18:13.004 --> 18:15.137
YOUR ROOMMATE/GIRLFRIEND
DIED?

18:15.181 --> 18:16.878
YEAH.

18:16.921 --> 18:19.098
I MEAN, NO.
SHE MOVED OUT.

18:19.141 --> 18:21.317
SORRY. DOESN'T COMPARE.
NOT EVEN REMOTELY.

18:21.361 --> 18:24.842
YOU'RE NOT COMPLETELY ALONE,
THOUGH.

18:24.886 --> 18:26.496
A GOLDEN RETRIEVER,
RIGHT?

18:26.540 --> 18:29.020
YEAH -- DIGBY, WHO WOULD
BE A SOURCE OF COMFORT

18:29.064 --> 18:30.631
IF HE DIDN'T PREFER LIVING

18:30.674 --> 18:33.373
WITH MY GIRLFRIEND,
HER NEW BESTY, AND THEIR PIG.

18:36.898 --> 18:39.161
YOU AWARE THAT JOE WORKED
AS A FRIEND-FOR-HIRE, MANN?

18:39.205 --> 18:41.381
WELL, I THOUGHT HE WAS
A TUTOR TO SPECIAL FOLKS

18:41.424 --> 18:42.947
OR SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

18:42.991 --> 18:45.036
MM-HMM. KNOW WHO HE WAS WITH
THE NIGHT HE DIED?

18:45.080 --> 18:46.821
SURE DON'T, PAL.

18:46.864 --> 18:48.170
UH, WAIT.

18:48.214 --> 18:49.998
WHERE DO YOU THINK
YOU'RE GOING?

18:50.041 --> 18:51.695
BEDROOMS ARE BACK HERE, RIGHT?
I JUST WANT TO SEE JOE'S.

18:51.739 --> 18:53.175
WISH YOU COULD,
BUT YOU CAN'T.

18:53.219 --> 18:54.959
SEE, I'M -- I'M LATE
FOR SOMETHING.

18:55.003 --> 18:57.223
BUT SERIOUSLY,
COME BACK ANYTIME.

19:10.279 --> 19:11.802
Calista:
RANDY'S A NUTJOB'S NAME.

19:11.846 --> 19:13.152
RANDY'S ALSO
A FUN GUY'S NAME.

19:13.195 --> 19:14.762
YOU CAN GRAB A BEER
WITH RANDY,

19:14.805 --> 19:17.025
GRILL A BRAT WITH RANDY,
PICK UP CHICKS WITH RANDY.

19:17.068 --> 19:19.419
AND HELP STUFF THEM INTO
RANDY'S FREEZER WITH RANDY.

19:19.462 --> 19:21.290
CAN YOU BE A LITTLE NICE?
HIS ROOMMATE DIED.

19:21.334 --> 19:23.336
DID YOU SEE HOW NICE AND CRAZY
BEHIND THE EYES HE GOT

19:23.379 --> 19:24.511
WHEN I TRIED TO GET
INTO THAT BACK ROOM?

19:24.554 --> 19:26.208
WHAT'S HE HIDING
IN THERE?

19:26.252 --> 19:27.557
PEOPLE ARE PRIVATE. I'VE NEVER
SEEN YOUR BACK ROOM.

19:27.601 --> 19:29.342
I'VE NEVER SEEN
YOUR FRONT ROOM.

19:29.385 --> 19:31.605
I'VE NEVER SEEN YOUR FRONT DOOR.
WHERE DO YOU LIVE, ANYWAY?

19:31.648 --> 19:34.347
YOUR SON'S
VERY SECRETIVE.
WELL, HE DIDN'T GET IT FROM
ME.

19:34.390 --> 19:36.000
MY HEEZY AIN'T
NONE OF Y'ALL'S BEEZY.

19:36.044 --> 19:37.437
RANDY MANN IS SHADY,

19:37.480 --> 19:38.829
AND I'M GONNA GET
BACK INTO HIS HOUSE

19:38.873 --> 19:40.875
AS SOON AS I GET HIM
TO TAKE THAT BAIT.

19:40.918 --> 19:42.442
MEANWHILE,
WHAT DO YOU GOT?

19:42.485 --> 19:44.705
STILL NO NEWS ON DOWNY,
AND SINCE COMPANY POLICY

19:44.748 --> 19:46.837
DICTATES THAT FRESCORTS
CAN'T DATE,

19:46.881 --> 19:47.969
THEN IT MAY EVEN BE
A DEAD END.

19:48.012 --> 19:50.101
HIYA, NED!
Hiya, bait.

19:50.145 --> 19:52.147
I FOUND YOUR FREE
COOKING-CLASS COUPON,

19:52.191 --> 19:53.540
SO I BROUGHT ALONG OFFAL.

19:53.583 --> 19:55.585
"AWFUL"?
OFFAL. O-F-F-A-L.

19:55.629 --> 19:57.935
ANIMAL ORGANS AND INNARDS
FOR MEAT PIE.

19:57.979 --> 20:00.329
Yeah, so "awful,"
like this idea.

20:00.373 --> 20:02.679
I'm not leaving Ned alone
with back-room Randy.

20:02.723 --> 20:05.682
This place is full of freezers
perfect for body-stuffing.

20:05.726 --> 20:07.118
It's also full of customers.

20:07.162 --> 20:10.296
HEY, COME ON IN,
RANDY! [ CHUCKLES ]

20:10.339 --> 20:12.776
ALRIGHT, GIRLS NUMBER ONE
AND TWO, GET TO FRESCORTING.

20:12.820 --> 20:14.038
ALRIGHT, MA,
LET'S GO.
[ BEEPING ]

20:14.082 --> 20:16.693
DAMN IT.
MY TARGET'S ON THE MOVE.

20:16.737 --> 20:18.478
WELL, CAN'T IT WAIT?

20:18.521 --> 20:20.436
I THOUGHT WE WERE GONNA GET
A CHANCE TO CATCH UP AND TALK

20:20.480 --> 20:22.438
WHILE WE WERE TOSSING
THAT APARTMENT.

20:22.482 --> 20:26.050
DARLING, YOU KNOW WHAT IT IS
TO BE MARRIED TO THE JOB.

20:26.094 --> 20:28.662
WE'LL HAVE TIME
FOR TALKING TOMORROW.

20:28.705 --> 20:30.185
Narrator:
THE WEIGHT OF THE UNTRUTHS

20:30.229 --> 20:32.318
ABOUT HIS MISSING DAUGHTER
GREW HEAVIER --

20:32.361 --> 20:36.539
SO HEAVY THAT HE FELT HE'D SOON
BE CRUSHED BENEATH THEM.

20:36.583 --> 20:39.890
AND SO HE ENTERED THE APARTMENT
OF A SUSPECTED KILLER

20:39.934 --> 20:42.153
WITH A DIFFERENT DEATH
ON HIS MIND --

20:42.197 --> 20:45.679
THAT OF HIS AND HIS MOTHER'S
FRIENDSHIP.

20:45.722 --> 20:48.247
"TUTOR OF SOME SORT,"
MY GLUE STICK.

20:57.691 --> 20:59.432
FREEZE!

21:10.660 --> 21:13.228
HOLY NOAH'S
NUTTY-AS-A-FRUITCAKE ARK.

21:15.578 --> 21:16.884
[ SHUDDERS ]

21:22.542 --> 21:25.022
Narrator: BUT THE MENAGERIE
OF TAXIDERMIED ANIMALS

21:25.066 --> 21:28.243
WOULD NOT BE THE NUTTIEST THING
EMERSON COD WOULD FIND.

21:45.173 --> 21:46.087
AREN'T YOU GONNA
CHOW DOWN?

21:46.130 --> 21:47.523
I'M A VEGETARIAN.

21:47.567 --> 21:49.351
THIS STUFF
WILL MAKE YOU STRONG.

21:49.395 --> 21:52.702
[ As woman ] GOBBLING
GIZZARDS MAKES MUSCLES.

21:52.746 --> 21:55.052
[ Normal voice ] AT LEAST
THAT'S WHAT MY MA USED TO SAY.

21:55.096 --> 21:56.750
UM, WHY?

21:56.793 --> 21:59.796
I HAD LOOSE LIGAMENTS
AS A KID -- ALWAYS FALLING,

21:59.840 --> 22:02.016
BRUISING MY TAILBONE,
BUMPING MY HEAD.

22:02.059 --> 22:04.453
A TOTAL DISASTER,
ESPECIALLY AT SPORTS.

22:04.497 --> 22:07.238
ALL THE KIDS AT SCHOOL MADE FUN,
BUT I DIDN'T CARE.

22:07.282 --> 22:09.502
I JUST PLAYED WITH MY PETS

22:09.545 --> 22:13.201
'CAUSE PETS ARE COOL WITH YOU,
NO MATTER WHAT...

22:13.244 --> 22:14.333
LIKE YOUR DOG.

22:14.376 --> 22:16.639
DIGBY, RIGHT?

22:16.683 --> 22:20.034
HE DIGS YOU JUST THE WAY
YOU ARE -- FOREVER WILL, TOO!

22:20.077 --> 22:22.558
I GOT TO STOP GOING ON
ABOUT STUFF LIKE THIS.

22:22.602 --> 22:24.778
IT MAKES ME SEEM
LIKE A WEIRDO.

22:24.821 --> 22:28.172
Narrator: HOWEVER, THE PIE MAKER
DID NOT SEE A WEIRDO.

22:28.216 --> 22:29.565
I DIDN'T HAVE ANY FRIENDS
AT SCHOOL, EITHER.

22:29.609 --> 22:31.045
TALK ABOUT A DISASTER
AT SPORTS --

22:31.088 --> 22:32.873
THEY WOULDN'T EVEN
GIVE ME GYM CLOTHES.

22:32.916 --> 22:34.744
INSTEAD, I'D SNEAK OFF ON MY OWN
AND BAKE PIES.

22:34.788 --> 22:36.529
THAT'S HOW I GOT STARTED
IN MY HOBBY, TOO.

22:36.572 --> 22:38.139
I DON'T USUALLY
SHARE IT WITH PEOPLE,

22:38.182 --> 22:41.229
BUT THE MINUTE WE MET,
I KNEW YOU'D BE OKAY.

22:41.272 --> 22:43.710
SO I BROUGHT IT ALONG
AND HID IT OUT BACK.

22:43.753 --> 22:44.537
YOU WANT TO SEE?

22:44.580 --> 22:45.973
S-SURE.

22:50.238 --> 22:51.631
DIGBY!

22:54.329 --> 22:55.591
LISTEN.

22:55.635 --> 22:56.766
HE'S SINGING "AMERICAN PIE"
FOR YOU.

22:56.810 --> 22:58.333
YOU KILLED MY DOG?!

22:58.377 --> 23:00.901
NO, NO, NO.
THAT'S BUTTERSCOTCH, MY DOG.

23:00.944 --> 23:02.946
YOU SAID YOUR GOLDEN RETRIEVER
WAS STAYING WITH SOMEONE ELSE,

23:02.990 --> 23:04.687
SO I THOUGHT
I'D LEND YOU MINE.

23:04.731 --> 23:06.036
HE'S BEEN MY BEST FRIEND
SINCE I WAS 5.

23:06.080 --> 23:07.908
THIS IS HOW YOU REPAY HIM?

23:07.951 --> 23:09.692
IF YOU HAD THE CHANCE
TO HOLD ON TO SOMEONE YOU LOVED

23:09.736 --> 23:11.912
AFTER HE OR SHE DIED,
WOULDN'T YOU?

23:11.955 --> 23:14.654
Narrator: IN FACT,
THE PIE MAKER HAD...TWICE.

23:14.697 --> 23:16.482
BUT INSTEAD HE SAID...

23:16.525 --> 23:17.657
PLEASE LEAVE.

23:20.486 --> 23:22.792
I THOUGHT WE HAD
SOMETHING IN COMMON.

23:22.836 --> 23:24.838
YOU'RE A SICK MAN,
RANDY MANN.

23:24.881 --> 23:26.100
STUFFING ALL THEM CRITTERS

23:26.143 --> 23:27.841
AND THEN POSING THEM
IN TWISTED WAYS.

23:27.884 --> 23:29.451
WELL, THAT'S --

23:29.495 --> 23:31.061
THAT'S WHY I DON'T EVER
TELL PEOPLE ABOUT IT.

23:31.105 --> 23:32.498
THEY DON'T UNDERSTAND.

23:32.541 --> 23:33.324
YOU DON'T THINK
IT'S TWISTED, DO YOU?

23:33.368 --> 23:34.413
OF COURSE HE DOES.

23:34.456 --> 23:36.197
HE WAS JUST HERE
BABYSITTING

23:36.240 --> 23:38.112
WHILE I WAS GATHERING EVIDENCE
AGAINST YOUR MURDERING ASS.

23:38.155 --> 23:39.330
LIAR. LIAR!

23:39.374 --> 23:41.071
YOUR PANTS ON FIRE.

23:41.115 --> 23:42.377
YOU WASN'T JOE'S ROOMMATE.
YOU WERE HIS CLIENT.

23:42.421 --> 23:44.510
WHY WOULD I TELL YOU
ABOUT THAT?

23:44.553 --> 23:47.034
IT'S EMBARRASSING,
HAVING TO PAY SOMEONE
TO HANG OUT WITH YOU.

23:47.077 --> 23:50.080
EVEN MORE HUMILIATING
TO HAVE YOUR FRESCORT REPO'ed.

23:50.124 --> 23:52.300
THAT MUST'VE BEEN THE FINAL
STRAW BEFORE YOU OFFED JOE.

23:52.343 --> 23:56.086
I OFFERED HIM A DEAL --
TO BE MY ROOMMATE RENT-FREE.

23:56.130 --> 23:59.438
HE AGREED. HE SAID IT'D BE
LIKE A REAL FRIENDSHIP.

23:59.481 --> 24:01.744
IS THAT WHY
YOU KEPT A PIECE OF HIM?

24:01.788 --> 24:04.704
JOE'S APPENDIX,
FLOATING IN FORMALDEHYDE.

24:04.747 --> 24:06.749
OH, GOD.
EXCEPT YOU FOUND OUT
REAL QUICK

24:06.793 --> 24:08.098
THAT PRESERVING A HUMAN
IS TOUGHER THAN A CHIPMUNK,

24:08.142 --> 24:09.491
SO YOU HAD TO
DUMP THE BODY.

24:09.535 --> 24:11.711
THAT APPENDIX IS MINE,
FORMERLY JOE'S.

24:11.754 --> 24:14.409
HE GAVE IT TO ME AS A JOKE
AND TO THANK ME

24:14.453 --> 24:16.716
FOR TAKING HIM TO THE HOSPITAL
WHEN IT BURST.

24:16.759 --> 24:19.109
CHECK HIS MEDICAL RECORDS
OR ASK HIS GIRLFRIEND.

24:19.153 --> 24:21.198
I MEAN, HE MUST'VE
TOLD HER ABOUT IT.

24:21.242 --> 24:23.723
WHAT'S HER NAME?
I DON'T KNOW,
BUT IT WAS SOMEONE AT WORK.

24:23.766 --> 24:25.812
MUST'VE BEEN SERIOUS,
THOUGH.

24:25.855 --> 24:31.165
JOE WAS EVEN GONNA QUIT
SO THEY COULD BE TOGETHER.

24:31.208 --> 24:32.471
MM.

24:34.037 --> 24:36.300
SO, NED JUST PAGED ME
AT THE WELCOME DESK,

24:36.344 --> 24:38.433
AND HE SAID THERE IS NO DOUBT
THERE IS A DOWNY AMONG US.

24:38.477 --> 24:40.522
OKAY, I'LL NOSE THROUGH

24:40.566 --> 24:43.264
MY "HOW TO FLATTER AND
REASSURE
THE PROFOUNDLY UGLY"
SYMPOSIUM.

24:43.307 --> 24:45.440
AND I'VE GOT A "CD MIXES
THAT MATTER" LAB IN 5 MINUTES,

24:45.484 --> 24:46.876
SO MAYBE SOMEONE THERE
WILL KNOW.

24:46.920 --> 24:49.531
"KINSHIP." ANYONE KNOW
ANOTHER WORD FOR IT?

24:49.575 --> 24:52.012
I'M AFRAID
THERE'S A "Q" INVOLVED.

24:52.055 --> 24:54.144
PROPINQUITY.
NICE.

24:54.188 --> 24:54.841
OKAY.

24:54.884 --> 24:55.972
GIVE ME ANOTHER.

24:56.016 --> 24:58.975
OH, 4-ACROSS
IS "GELDING."

24:59.019 --> 25:02.544
THANKS, BUT, UM,
I DON'T DO THE ACROSSES.

25:02.588 --> 25:05.112
I ONLY DO THE...
DOWNS.

25:05.155 --> 25:06.243
BARB, YOU'RE DOWNY.

25:06.287 --> 25:08.028
NO, I'M NOT.

25:08.071 --> 25:10.204
YOU SURE AREN'T F-F-F-FAKING
ANYTHING TO THE CONTRARY.

25:12.162 --> 25:15.775
[ Sobbing ]
OKAY. OKAY.

25:15.818 --> 25:17.733
Chuck: IT'S OKAY.
WE'RE JUST TRYING TO HELP.

25:17.777 --> 25:20.867
IS "DOWNY" A NICKNAME
THAT JOE GAVE YOU?

25:20.910 --> 25:21.650
TISSUE.
WHAT?

25:21.694 --> 25:23.260
TISSUE!

25:23.304 --> 25:25.611
TISSUE.
I-I CAN'T REACH THAT.
I JUST --

25:26.742 --> 25:28.527
[ SOBBING CONTINUES ]

25:28.570 --> 25:30.137
AAH! AAH!

25:30.180 --> 25:31.617
BARB, DON'T!

25:31.660 --> 25:32.835
FAKE THAT, BITCHES!

25:33.967 --> 25:35.316
[ CREAKING ]

25:37.448 --> 25:38.058
[ CLATTERING ]

25:38.101 --> 25:39.102
CRAP.

25:39.146 --> 25:40.800
[ DOOR OPENS ]
AHA!

25:46.545 --> 25:48.372
[ GLASS SHATTERS ]

25:49.635 --> 25:51.288
[ GAGGING ]

25:53.595 --> 25:55.423
OH, HELL, NO.

25:59.427 --> 26:00.689
MAMA.
YES, DEAR?

26:00.733 --> 26:02.386
I CAN'T BREATHE.
YEAH?

26:02.430 --> 26:05.259
I GAVE YOU BREATH,
AND THIS IS THE THANKS I GET?

26:06.652 --> 26:09.263
Narrator:
THE FACTS WERE THESE --

26:09.306 --> 26:10.743
MISSY SCRIVNER,

26:10.786 --> 26:13.006
EDITORIAL ASSISTANT
AT BOOK 'EM BOOKS,

26:13.049 --> 26:16.400
OVERSAW ALL REJECTED
MANUSCRIPT LETTERS.

26:16.444 --> 26:20.230
UNDERBITE SURGERY HAD LEFT THE
GIRL SHACKLED TO A LIQUID DIET,

26:20.274 --> 26:22.493
WHICH FOUND ITS WAY
ONTO THE REJECTION LETTER

26:22.537 --> 26:24.626
OF ONE EMERSON COD.

26:24.670 --> 26:28.325
UNABLE TO DECIPHER ANYTHING
BUT THE WORDS "E" AND "COD,"
[ MUMBLING ]

26:28.369 --> 26:30.545
MISSY PHONED
DIRECTORY ASSISTANCE.

26:30.589 --> 26:33.417
MISTAKING HER GARBLED "E"
FOR A "C,"

26:33.461 --> 26:35.594
THE OPERATOR
GAVE THE ADDRESS OF CALISTA,

26:35.637 --> 26:37.073
WHO READ THE CRITIQUES

26:37.117 --> 26:39.815
AND ASSUMED
HER SON'S SECRET BOOK WAS...

26:39.859 --> 26:41.556
A THINLY DISGUISED
TELL-ALL

26:41.600 --> 26:43.645
TO SHOW THE WORLD WHAT KIND
OF HORRIBLE MOTHER I AM!

26:43.689 --> 26:45.386
NO.
DID YOU EVEN READ IT?

26:45.429 --> 26:48.084
DIDN'T HAVE TO. THE COVER
SCREAMS "SMEAR CAMPAIGN."

26:48.128 --> 26:49.651
AND WHAT'S WITH THE MAIN
CHARACTER BEING A GIRL?

26:49.695 --> 26:51.174
YOU SAYING
I TURNED YOU GAY?

26:51.218 --> 26:53.655
I AIN'T GAY,
AND THIS AIN'T ABOUT YOU!

26:53.699 --> 26:55.004
IT'S ABOUT MY DAUGHTER!

26:55.048 --> 26:56.832
WHAT DAUGHTER?

26:56.876 --> 27:00.662
SHE'S 7. HER MAMA RAN OFF
WITH HER WHEN SHE WAS A BABY.

27:00.706 --> 27:04.057
I'VE BEEN LOOKING FOR HER
EVER SINCE, WITH NO LUCK.

27:04.100 --> 27:06.929
AND THAT'S WHY I FINALLY WROTE
"LIL' GUM SHOE" --

27:06.973 --> 27:12.892
TO HELP HER
HAVE A WAY TO FIND ME.

27:12.935 --> 27:14.458
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME?

27:14.502 --> 27:16.112
I DIDN'T EVEN
TELL MY FRIENDS.

27:16.156 --> 27:17.984
WELL, I'M NOT YOUR FRIEND.
I'M YOUR MOTHER.

27:18.027 --> 27:20.726
Oh, now you're my mama.
WHAT'S THAT, MUMBLES?

27:20.769 --> 27:22.379
I SAID...

27:22.423 --> 27:23.946
YOU ONLY SAY STUFF LIKE THAT

27:23.990 --> 27:25.731
WHEN YOU WANT ME TO FEEL
GUILTY ABOUT SOMETHING.

27:25.774 --> 27:27.646
WELL, SINCE YOU SWITCHED
BACK TO MAMA MODE,

27:27.689 --> 27:28.951
I GUESS
I CAN ROLL WITH THAT.

27:28.995 --> 27:30.561
SO, TELL ME, MAMA...

27:30.605 --> 27:32.607
WHAT KIND OF MOTHER
SPIES ON HER OWN SON?!

27:32.651 --> 27:34.914
IT'S NOT LIKE I WANTED TO.

27:34.957 --> 27:37.699
DAMN.
THAT'S SHREWD, WOMAN.

27:37.743 --> 27:40.049
YOU FAKED A FRAUD CASE.

27:40.093 --> 27:42.704
YOU SET OFF
YOUR OWN BEEPER.

27:42.748 --> 27:45.446
YOU EVEN MADE SURE
I TOOK TWO CLIENTS AT ONCE

27:45.489 --> 27:47.666
SO I'D BE DOUBLY BUSY.

27:47.709 --> 27:51.539
ALL SO YOU COULD POKE AROUND
IN MY PERSONAL LIFE.

27:51.582 --> 27:53.628
YOU KNOW WHAT
THE SAD THING IS, MAMA?

27:53.672 --> 27:56.152
I WAS GONNA
TELL YOU EVERYTHING.

27:56.196 --> 27:57.763
[ GRUMBLES ]

27:57.806 --> 27:59.852
WHAT KIND OF FOOL
DO YOU TAKE ME FOR?

28:02.071 --> 28:04.160
ARE YOU SAYING
YOU DON'T BELIEVE ME?

28:06.728 --> 28:08.121
WELL, I GUESS
THERE'S NOTHING ELSE

28:08.164 --> 28:10.297
FOR YOU AND ME
TO TALK ABOUT, THEN.

28:11.907 --> 28:14.605
CHUCK AND OLIVE
HAVEN'T CHECKED IN YET.

28:14.649 --> 28:16.564
Olive: IT'S LIKE
WE'RE TRAPPED IN A SACHET

28:16.607 --> 28:18.479
IN A PANTY DRAWER
OF A DEAD SHUT-IN

28:18.522 --> 28:20.307
WHO WAS SHUT IN HER BEDROOM
BY HER CAT

28:20.350 --> 28:24.528
SO THAT IT WOULDN'T HAVE TO
SMELL THE STENCH OF FREESIA.

28:24.572 --> 28:25.399
[ Gagging ]
CAN'T YOU SMELL IT?

28:25.442 --> 28:26.922
YEP.
[ COUGHS ]

28:26.966 --> 28:29.925
THAT WOULD BE
MY FREESIA HAIR DETANGLER

28:29.969 --> 28:32.449
THAT YOU SAID SMELLS AMAZING
YESTERDAY.

28:32.493 --> 28:34.930
WISH I HADN'T NOW!
WISH I HADN'T TOLD YOU THOSE
CAPRIS MADE YOU LOOK TALLER!

28:34.974 --> 28:36.845
LIAR!

28:36.889 --> 28:39.979
NO, I'M A TRUTH-AR,
BECAUSE I CAME CLEAN UNPROMPTED,

28:40.022 --> 28:42.764
WHEREAS YOU ONLY ADMITTED TO
LYING BECAUSE YOU GOT CAUGHT.

28:42.808 --> 28:44.461
HERE COMES
THE CENTER OF THE UNIVERSE

28:44.505 --> 28:47.508
PULLING US ALL INTO HER
GRAVITATIONAL ORBIT OF BLAME.

28:47.551 --> 28:48.857
OH, WELL, F.Y.I...

28:48.901 --> 28:50.772
UM, THERE IS
NO CENTER OF THE UNIVERSE,

28:50.816 --> 28:53.949
BECAUSE OUR UNIVERSE
IS FOREVER EXPANDING.

28:53.993 --> 28:55.603
LIKE YOUR NEEDINESS.

28:55.646 --> 28:58.780
"WAH, RESPECT MY FEELINGS.
WAH, DON'T FENCE ME IN.

28:58.824 --> 29:00.695
WAH, DON'T TREAT ME
LIKE I'M DEAD."

29:00.739 --> 29:04.133
WELL, IF YOU'RE SO DEAD,
HOW CAN YOU BE SO NEEDY?

29:04.177 --> 29:05.787
OH, RIGHT --
YOU'RE SELFISH!

29:05.831 --> 29:07.615
I AM SELFISH?

29:07.658 --> 29:10.487
I'VE JUST SHARED WITH YOU
EVERY SINGLE THING THAT I OWN.

29:10.531 --> 29:12.402
BIG WHOOP!
SECOND HAND STUFF.

29:12.446 --> 29:13.926
OH, SO THAT'S WHAT
YOU'RE ANGRY ABOUT,

29:13.969 --> 29:15.536
THE ONE THING
I WON'T SHARE -- NED.

29:15.579 --> 29:17.190
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU JUST SAID THAT.

29:17.233 --> 29:18.539
DON'T SHRUG AT ME IN THE DARK,
CHARLOTTE CHARLES.

29:18.582 --> 29:20.628
THAT WAS A LOW BLOW!

29:20.671 --> 29:23.718
WHAT DO YOU EXPECT ME TO DO?
I'M IN A NO-WIN SITUATION HERE.

29:23.762 --> 29:26.416
I CAN'T TALK TO YOU ABOUT IT
BECAUSE THAT'D BE INSENSITIVE.

29:26.460 --> 29:27.766
I CAN'T TALK TO NED
ABOUT IT

29:27.809 --> 29:29.506
BECAUSE HE'S DONE
NOTHING WRONG.

29:29.550 --> 29:31.465
I MEAN,
IF I WERE TO HAVE A NICKEL

29:31.508 --> 29:33.597
FOR EVERY SINGLE TIME
THE THREE OF US ARE TOGETHER

29:33.641 --> 29:36.862
AND UNEXPECTEDLY, ACCIDENTALLY,
I CATCH YOU LOOKING AT HIM --

29:36.905 --> 29:38.298
NO. STOP TALKING.
STOP TALKING.

29:38.341 --> 29:40.082
HELP! HELP US!
ANYONE, HELP!

29:40.126 --> 29:42.606
AND YOU HAVE THIS LITTLE,
SAD, PINING LOOK ON YOUR FACE

29:42.650 --> 29:46.001
OF "OHH, OHH, NED.
WHY CAN'T YOU LOVE ME?"

29:46.045 --> 29:47.742
AND THEN I FEEL LIKE
A COMPLETE JERK

29:47.786 --> 29:49.657
FOR BEING IN LOVE
WITH MY OWN BOYFRIEND.

29:49.700 --> 29:52.094
YEAH, A BOYFRIEND
YOU DON'T TOUCH.

29:52.138 --> 29:54.227
I TOLD YOU -- WE CAN'T!

29:54.270 --> 29:56.490
THAT DOESN'T
MAKE ANY SENSE!

29:57.839 --> 30:00.233
I'M GOING HOME!
TO MY HOME!

30:01.234 --> 30:02.409
WHAT HAPPENED?

30:02.452 --> 30:04.237
ROOMMATE SQUABBLE
BROUGHT ON

30:04.280 --> 30:06.761
BY THE SUSPICIOUS ACTIONS
OF BARB, A.K.A. DOWNY,

30:06.805 --> 30:07.980
WHO IS DEFINITELY
A PERSON OF INTEREST.

30:08.023 --> 30:09.808
GOT A NAME AND ADDRESS
ON HER?

30:09.851 --> 30:12.680
NO, BUT I KNOW WHERE I CAN
GET ONE -- BUDDY'S OFFICE.

30:12.723 --> 30:14.160
[ DOOR CREAKS ]

30:14.203 --> 30:15.944
OH, NO! BARB!

30:20.906 --> 30:23.038
OH, GOOD, KITTY,
YOU GOT OUT OF THE LOCKER.

30:23.082 --> 30:24.997
SORRY ABOUT THAT. I THOUGHT
YOU WERE GONNA TELL ON ME.

30:25.040 --> 30:27.434
FOR WHAT, KILLING JOE?
NO, FOR DATING HIM.

30:27.477 --> 30:30.829
SEE, I DIDN'T WANT TO GET FIRED.
THIS JOB'S THE ONLY PL--

30:30.872 --> 30:32.178
[ GASPING ]

30:32.221 --> 30:33.179
Ned:
HER LUNGS ARE CRUSHED.

30:33.222 --> 30:34.963
WHO KNOWS CPR?

30:38.924 --> 30:40.142
OH, GOOD IDEA.

30:40.186 --> 30:41.927
OKAY, BREATHE.
BREATHE. BREATHE.

30:41.970 --> 30:43.189
[ PUMPING ]

30:44.973 --> 30:46.801
...THE ONLY PLACE
MY RELENTLESS POSITIVITY

30:46.845 --> 30:49.369
AND ENCYCLOPEDIC KNOWLEDGE OF
HAIR BRAIDING MEANT SOMETHING.

30:49.412 --> 30:51.937
I COULDN'T HURT JOE.
WHEN HE WAS AROUND,
I COULD BE MY TRUE SELF.

30:51.980 --> 30:53.547
ONLY NOW I'LL NEVER KNOW

30:53.590 --> 30:55.114
IF IT WAS JUST OUR
MUTUAL PASSION FOR CROSSWORDS

30:55.157 --> 30:57.638
THAT BROUGHT US TOGETHER
OR IF HE FELT THE SAME WAY.

30:57.681 --> 31:00.206
YOU WERE HIS ONE-AND-ONLY.
HE WAS ABOUT TO LEAVE
THE COMPANY FOR YOU.

31:00.249 --> 31:03.209
OHH. HE SAID HE HAD SOMETHING
IMPORTANT TO TELL ME.

31:03.252 --> 31:05.124
THE NIGHT HE DIED,
I WAITED FOR HIS CALL,

31:05.167 --> 31:07.648
BUT HE NEVER MADE IT BACK
FROM HIS FRESCORTING GIG.

31:07.691 --> 31:09.606
WAIT A MINUTE.
JOE DIDN'T WORK THAT NIGHT.

31:09.650 --> 31:12.479
HE WAS MOONLIGHTING --
A STANDING SPORTS DATE.
WHO WITH?

31:12.522 --> 31:14.916
JOE NEVER SAID,
BUT THE GUY SOUNDED TRAGIC.

31:14.960 --> 31:17.266
TWO YEARS OF PLAYING BALL,
AND HE WAS STILL A SPAZ.

31:17.310 --> 31:19.486
SOME CLIENTS SIMPLY LACK
THE JOCK GENE.

31:19.529 --> 31:21.227
BUDDY CALLS THEM
BLEACHER LEECHERS.

31:21.270 --> 31:23.142
YEAH, SKIP TO THE PART WHERE
YOU BECOME THE MAIN SQUEEZE.

31:23.185 --> 31:25.013
I WAS HAVING A MELTDOWN,

31:25.057 --> 31:27.842
CAME IN FOR A HUG,
PRETENDED THOSE ARMS WERE
JOE'S.

31:27.886 --> 31:29.888
THAT'S WHEN THE DIAL GOT
TURNED TO 11 BY THE SPARTAN.

31:31.585 --> 31:33.587
I TRIED TO FIGHT --
GRABBED THIS FROM HIS HELMET.

31:33.630 --> 31:34.980
YOU DID GOOD, BARB.

31:37.504 --> 31:39.767
THERE'S NO SPARTAN RUNNING
AROUND KILLING THE POPULAR
KIDS.

31:39.810 --> 31:41.508
THIS AIN'T
THERMOPYLAE HIGH.

31:41.551 --> 31:44.859
RIGHT. IT'S SPARTANBURG WEST
AND BUDDY'S TEAM MASCOT.

31:44.903 --> 31:46.948
GREAT. HOW ARE WE GONNA
FIND OUT WHO THAT WAS?

31:46.992 --> 31:49.255
I'M HAVING THE MOST
UNFORTUNATE OF HUNCHES.

31:49.298 --> 31:52.954
RANDY WAS AN UNCOORDINATED
BLEACHER LEECHER.

31:52.998 --> 31:54.956
HE TOLD ME THE KIDS AT SCHOOL
TEASED HIM MERCILESSLY FOR IT.

31:55.000 --> 31:56.740
YEAH, AND MAYBE
ONE OF THOSE KIDS

31:56.784 --> 32:00.092
WAS VARSITY QUARTERBACK
AND SELF-PROCLAIMED DORK
MENACER

32:00.135 --> 32:01.397
BUDDY AMICUS.

32:01.441 --> 32:03.051
DETECTIVE COD,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

32:03.095 --> 32:04.966
WE'RE ONE STEP CLOSER
TO FINDING JOE'S KILLER.

32:05.010 --> 32:06.576
WITH KITTY?
YEAH, KITTY'S WITH ME.

32:06.620 --> 32:08.622
WHAT'S WRONG WITH BARB?
OH, SHE'S DEAD...

32:08.665 --> 32:10.363
THANKS TO
YOUR HAPPY-HUG MACHINE.

32:10.406 --> 32:12.104
NOT BARB.

32:12.147 --> 32:15.368
SWEET, ADORABLE,
CONCILIATORY BARB?

32:15.411 --> 32:17.283
WHO COULD DO SOMETHING
SO HORRIBLE?

32:17.326 --> 32:19.720
DOES THE NAME RANDY MANN
RING A BELL?

32:19.763 --> 32:21.069
SHOULD IT?

32:21.113 --> 32:22.897
WE THINK
HE'S YOUR OLD SCHOOL MASCOT.

32:22.941 --> 32:24.420
THE SPARTAN YOU TANGLED WITH
BACK IN THE DAY --

32:24.464 --> 32:25.987
HE'S BACK,
AND HE'S PISSED.

32:26.031 --> 32:29.512
DO YOU HAPPEN TO HAVE
A HIGH-SCHOOL YEARBOOK?

32:29.556 --> 32:31.906
THANK YOU.
I HAVE TO
EVACUATE THE BUILDING.

32:31.950 --> 32:33.342
SOMEONE CALL THE POLICE,

32:33.386 --> 32:34.778
TELL THEM
THERE'S A VINDICTIVE PERSON

32:34.822 --> 32:36.650
WITH LOW SELF-ESTEEM
ON THE LOOSE.

32:36.693 --> 32:38.608
THERE'S NO RANDY MANN
LISTED.

32:38.652 --> 32:40.741
MAYBE HE'S USING AN ALIAS.
THE PHONE'S DEAD.

32:40.784 --> 32:42.090
HELP!

32:42.134 --> 32:44.875
Emerson: HE GOT BUDDY.
LET'S MOVE.

32:44.919 --> 32:45.789
OH! WATCH OUT!

32:45.833 --> 32:46.965
OHH!

32:50.925 --> 32:52.753
THAT WAS CLOSE.

32:52.796 --> 32:57.062
YEAH. LAST THING WE NEED IS
ANOTHER DEAD BODY ON OUR HANDS.

32:57.105 --> 32:59.934
[ MUMBLING ]
OHH!
TOO LATE FOR THAT.

33:04.591 --> 33:06.419
WELL, HELLO.

33:06.462 --> 33:08.769
UH, THIS IS A SURPRISE.
FOR YOU, TOO, I'M SURE.

33:08.812 --> 33:10.249
WE'RE HAVING A LITTLE TROUBLE
GETTING A GOOD LOOK

33:10.292 --> 33:12.381
BECAUSE THERE'S
A MANNEQUIN FACE OVER YOURS.

33:12.425 --> 33:14.949
MAYBE IF YOU TOOK OFF
YOUR HELMET?

33:14.993 --> 33:16.037
OHH!
OHH! OHH!

33:16.081 --> 33:17.082
H-H-HELMET ON!
HELMET ON!

33:17.125 --> 33:18.953
Chuck:
SORRY ABOUT THAT.

33:18.997 --> 33:21.434
WE WEREN'T EXPECTING SUCH
A LEATHERY, MUMMY-LIKE, UM --

33:21.477 --> 33:24.306
CAN YOU SPEAK? WE WOULD REALLY
LIKE TO KNOW WHO YOU ARE.

33:25.916 --> 33:27.831
YOU'RE THE SPARTANBURG WEST
QUARTERBACK.

33:27.875 --> 33:29.833
CAN YOU SHOW US?

33:29.877 --> 33:31.922
"ARES KOSTOPOLOUS."

33:31.966 --> 33:33.533
WOW.
YOU WERE A HOTTIE.

33:33.576 --> 33:36.449
BUT BUDDY
WAS THE QUARTERBACK.

33:36.492 --> 33:38.842
BUDDY -- BUDDY
WAS THE SPARTAN MASCOT.

33:40.105 --> 33:41.062
OHH!

33:41.106 --> 33:42.585
BUDDY KILLED YOU, TOO!

33:44.022 --> 33:45.632
SO, THE BUDDY AMICUS LEGEND

33:45.675 --> 33:47.503
OF BEING A HIGH-SCHOOL
GOLDEN BOY IS A COMPLETE LIE.

33:47.547 --> 33:48.939
AND A TOTAL HORROR SHOW.

33:48.983 --> 33:51.464
WHAT KIND OF PERSON
HOLDS ON TO A DEAD BODY?

33:51.507 --> 33:53.944
THE KIND THAT WANTS
TO PRESERVE A FRIENDSHIP.

33:53.988 --> 33:55.468
[ SHRIEKS ]

33:55.511 --> 33:56.904
Narrator:
THE FACTS WERE THESE.

33:59.124 --> 34:02.649
AS A TEEN, BUDDY AMICUS
WAS UNKNOWN AND INVISIBLE.

34:03.650 --> 34:05.260
AS VARSITY QUARTERBACK,

34:05.304 --> 34:10.091
ARES KOSTOPOLOUS
WAS ADMIRED BY ALL.

34:10.135 --> 34:12.354
IN HIS FRAGILE
AND OBSESSED MIND,

34:12.398 --> 34:15.879
BUDDY WAS BEST FRIENDS
WITH THE BIG MAN ON CAMPUS,

34:15.923 --> 34:18.056
AND HE HAD TO GET CLOSER,
NO MATTER WHAT.

34:18.795 --> 34:20.101
SPARTANS!

34:21.842 --> 34:23.800
Narrator:
THE NAMELESS, FACELESS MASCOT

34:23.844 --> 34:26.586
STROVE TO MAKE
HIS PIGSKIN GOD PROUD,

34:26.629 --> 34:30.068
BUT NO ONE NOTICED HIM
UNTIL THE STATE CHAMPIONSHIPS,

34:30.111 --> 34:32.287
WHEN EVERYONE DID.

34:32.331 --> 34:33.941
SPARTANS!

34:33.984 --> 34:35.334
SPARTANS!

34:35.377 --> 34:36.639
WHOO!

34:36.683 --> 34:37.858
WHOO! SPART--

34:37.901 --> 34:38.685
OOPS.

34:38.728 --> 34:40.078
[ AIR HORN BLOWING ]

34:42.776 --> 34:45.257
Narrator: THE SPARTAN
FELT THE AGONY OF DEFEAT.

34:45.300 --> 34:47.302
BUT THERE WAS MORE AGONY
TO COME.

34:47.346 --> 34:48.651
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

34:50.262 --> 34:52.873
OW! OH!
GUYS, GUYS!

34:52.916 --> 34:54.135
[ CLOTH TEARING ]

34:59.227 --> 35:01.925
Narrator: BUDDY THOUGHT ARES,
HIS HERO, WOULD SAVE HIM.

35:03.666 --> 35:06.234
THE REALIZATION
THAT THEIR FRIENDSHIP WAS A LIE

35:06.278 --> 35:09.107
WAS SO PAINFUL,
IT DROVE BUDDY MAD...

35:11.196 --> 35:13.241
AND MURDEROUS.

35:15.330 --> 35:17.158
[ SWORD PLUNGES ]

35:17.202 --> 35:20.509
YEARS OF DERMATOLOGY,
ORTHODONTICS, AND STEROID ABUSE

35:20.553 --> 35:22.337
TRANSFORMED BUDDY AMICUS

35:22.381 --> 35:24.861
INTO THE MAN
HE'D ALWAYS WANTED TO BE.

35:24.905 --> 35:27.168
HE FOUNDED
MY BEST FRIEND, INC.,

35:27.212 --> 35:30.345
AND FOUND,
AMONG HIS FRESCORTS, JOE,

35:30.389 --> 35:34.306
WHO TRIGGERED IN HIM A NEW,
ALBEIT FAMILIAR, OBSESSION.

35:34.349 --> 35:36.960
THIS TIME, BUDDY KNEW
THINGS WOULD BE DIFFERENT.

35:37.004 --> 35:39.180
NOW HE WAS
THE BIG MAN ON CAMPUS,

35:39.224 --> 35:42.009
ABLE TO BEFRIEND
ANYONE HE CHOSE...

35:42.052 --> 35:44.359
UNTIL THE DAY
JOE BROUGHT IT ALL TO AN END.

35:46.144 --> 35:49.669
HE WAS QUITTING
TO BE WITH FELLOW FRESCORT BARB,

35:49.712 --> 35:51.888
WHICH MEANT
HE WAS ALSO QUITTING BUDDY,

35:51.932 --> 35:54.587
NO MATTER HOW MUCH
THE DESPERATE, DELUSIONAL MAN

35:54.630 --> 35:57.155
OFFERED TO PAY HIM TO STAY.

35:57.198 --> 36:01.071
THE REALIZATION THAT ANOTHER
FRIENDSHIP HAD BEEN ANOTHER LIE

36:01.115 --> 36:03.596
DROVE BUDDY MAD AND MURDEROUS
YET AGAIN.

36:05.293 --> 36:10.472
AND SO, HE CONVINCED JOE
TO MEET FOR ONE LAST GAME.

36:10.516 --> 36:12.692
[ SWORD PLUNGES ]

36:12.735 --> 36:14.215
WHY'D YOU HEAVE-HO
THE BODY?

36:14.259 --> 36:17.175
I TRIED TO PRESERVE HIM
LIKE I PRESERVED ARES.

36:17.218 --> 36:19.873
SADLY, THE FORMALDEHYDE
TRIGGERED MY ASTHMA.

36:19.916 --> 36:22.354
AND BARB, SHE TOOK JOE,

36:22.397 --> 36:23.746
SO YOU TOOK HER LIFE.

36:23.790 --> 36:26.096
WANT TO KNOW
THE MOST SENSELESS THING?

36:26.140 --> 36:28.490
I STARTED THIS COMPANY
TO HELP PEOPLE

36:28.534 --> 36:30.623
SO THAT THE FRIENDLESS
WOULDN'T SUFFER AS I DID.

36:30.666 --> 36:32.625
OF COURSE THEY SUFFER.
I'VE SEEN IT UP CLOSE.

36:32.668 --> 36:34.583
AT FIRST THE BOGUS FRIENDSHIPS
YOU SELL SEEM GOOD,

36:34.627 --> 36:36.194
BUT DEEP DOWN,
THOSE CLIENTS NEVER STOP FEELING

36:36.237 --> 36:37.456
LIKE WEIRDOS
WHO NEED TO BE FIXED.

36:37.499 --> 36:39.066
AND SO THEY KEEP PAYING,

36:39.109 --> 36:41.416
HOPING THAT SOMEDAY
THOSE FEELINGS WILL GO AWAY,

36:41.460 --> 36:44.027
BUT THOSE FEELINGS
NEVER GO AWAY.

36:44.071 --> 36:45.855
AAH!

36:45.899 --> 36:48.249
I'M KILLING YOU FIRST.
SAY GOODBYE.

36:48.293 --> 36:49.816
GOODBYE, FRIEND.

36:51.731 --> 36:53.950
Narrator: WITH THE FRESCORT
KILLER BEHIND BARS,

36:53.994 --> 36:55.909
THE PIE MAKER
WAS FREE TO REVISIT

36:55.952 --> 36:57.867
A FORMER FRESCORT CLIENT.

36:57.911 --> 37:00.087
YOUR MEAT PIES.
I CAN'T EAT THEM, SO...

37:01.828 --> 37:05.092
THIS IS DIGBY, BY THE WAY.
DIGBY, SAY HI TO RANDY.

37:05.135 --> 37:06.180
[ BARKS ]

37:06.224 --> 37:08.878
OH, AREN'T YOU A NICE BOY?

37:08.922 --> 37:10.271
SO UNLIKE YOUR OWNER.

37:10.315 --> 37:12.752
I DESERVE THAT,
LIKE YOU DESERVE AN APOLOGY.

37:12.795 --> 37:14.493
APOLOGY ACCEPTED.
GOODBYE.

37:14.536 --> 37:18.497
WAIT. YOU DON'T HAVE TO PAY
FOR IT -- FRIENDSHIP.

37:18.540 --> 37:21.674
THE TRUTH IS, THERE ARE A LOT
OF PEOPLE LIKE YOU -- US --

37:21.717 --> 37:24.981
WITH STRANGE HOBBIES
OR TALENTS OR GIFTS

37:25.025 --> 37:26.418
THAT WE TRY TO HIDE
BECAUSE WE'RE AFRAID

37:26.461 --> 37:28.724
IT MAKES US SEEM WEIRD
OR TURNS PEOPLE OFF.

37:28.768 --> 37:32.293
BUT THAT'S A MISTAKE.

37:32.337 --> 37:33.773
WHAT MAKES ME UNIQUE

37:33.816 --> 37:36.254
HAS BROUGHT EVERY PERSON
I LOVE INTO MY LIFE,

37:37.777 --> 37:39.996
AND IT COULD BE
THE SAME FOR YOU.

37:40.040 --> 37:42.477
WELL, THERE'S NOTHING WRONG
WITH BEING ALONE, YOU KNOW.

37:42.521 --> 37:45.393
JOE TAUGHT ME THAT --
CALLED IT THE "FIRST STEP."

37:45.437 --> 37:47.047
YOU'RE NO GOOD
TO SOMEBODY ELSE

37:47.090 --> 37:48.831
UNLESS YOU'RE GOOD
WITH BEING WITH JUST YOU.

37:52.574 --> 37:55.621
Narrator: ADVICE AN ALONE
PIE MAKER COULD USE, AS WELL.

37:57.362 --> 38:00.669
THE PIE MAKER OBTAINED
BUDDY AMICUS' CLIENT LIST

38:00.713 --> 38:03.672
AND INVITED THOSE LISTED
TO BRING THEIR TRUE SELVES

38:03.716 --> 38:05.587
TO A LOW-KEY MIXER.

38:05.631 --> 38:07.328
AND WHILE THE INTENTION
WAS GOOD,

38:07.372 --> 38:10.810
THE EVENING
WAS AN UNMITIGATED DISASTER...

38:10.853 --> 38:12.594
UNTIL THE SECOND HOUR,

38:12.638 --> 38:15.945
WHEN EVERYONE FINALLY STARTED
TO COME OUT OF THEIR SHELLS.

38:17.382 --> 38:18.687
IN ANOTHER 10 MINUTES,

38:18.731 --> 38:19.775
I WAS GONNA PULL OUT
THE TEQUILA SHOTS,

38:19.819 --> 38:21.168
AND IF THAT DIDN'T WORK,

38:21.211 --> 38:23.083
PULL THE FIRE ALARM
AND CALL IT A DAY.

38:23.126 --> 38:24.824
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

38:24.867 --> 38:26.391
CAN YOU GIVE DIGBY
ANOTHER HUG?

38:26.434 --> 38:28.523
AW, YEAH,
OF COURSE I WILL.

38:28.567 --> 38:30.830
DO YOU WANT A HUG?
COME ON.

38:30.873 --> 38:33.963
TIGHTER. AND GIVE HIS BELLY
A RUBBA-RUBBA-RUBBA.

38:34.007 --> 38:36.966
YOU KNOW, IF YOU WANT,
I CAN HUG HIM ALL NIGHT LONG

38:37.010 --> 38:40.840
WHEN I SLEEP OVER
AT YOUR PLACE...PERMANENTLY.

38:40.883 --> 38:42.755
DID I FORGET TO TELL YOU
THAT I'M MOVING BACK IN?

38:42.798 --> 38:44.974
T-THAT SQUABBLE
WITH YOU AND OLIVE

38:45.018 --> 38:47.020
IS CLEARLY
MORE THAN A SQUABBLE.

38:47.063 --> 38:49.109
YEAH, WE LET LOOSE
WITH EVERYTHING WE WERE
FEELING AND THINKING

38:49.152 --> 38:50.589
AND FLOGGED OUR FRIENDSHIP
TO DEATH

38:50.632 --> 38:51.981
WITH A GREAT BIG TRUTH CLUB.

38:52.025 --> 38:55.202
DOES THAT MEAN
WHEN IT COMES TO US,

38:55.245 --> 38:57.030
I SHOULD KEEP MY TRUTHS
TO MYSELF?

38:57.073 --> 38:58.814
NO, OF COURSE NOT.

38:58.858 --> 39:00.947
HANG ON. AM I SETTING MYSELF UP
FOR SOMETHING HERE?

39:00.990 --> 39:02.383
I WAS SETTING MYSELF UP
TO TELL YOU

39:02.427 --> 39:03.602
THAT EVER SINCE
YOU MOVED IN WITH OLIVE,

39:03.645 --> 39:05.691
I FEEL LIKE
I NEVER SEE YOU ANYMORE.

39:05.734 --> 39:07.780
AND PLEASE DON'T TAKE THAT
ANY OTHER WAY THAN...

39:09.129 --> 39:11.174
I MISS YOU.

39:11.218 --> 39:13.786
THAT WAS REALLY SWEET.
I MISS YOU, TOO.

39:13.829 --> 39:16.136
ALL THE MORE REASON
FOR ME MOVING BACK IN.

39:16.179 --> 39:18.443
SORRY. YOU CAN'T.

39:18.486 --> 39:20.096
BUT YOU PROMISED ME
COMFORTING.

39:20.140 --> 39:22.447
YOU'RE MY KING-SIZED DUVET
OF GOOSE-DOWN GOODNESS.

39:22.490 --> 39:24.057
I KNOW.

39:24.100 --> 39:25.885
SELFISHLY, I WANT TO DUVET YOU
RIGHT THIS SECOND,

39:25.928 --> 39:28.061
BUT I'VE GOT TO WORK ON
BEING OKAY WITH BEING ALONE,

39:28.104 --> 39:31.412
AND YOU'VE GOT TO WORK ON
YOUR FRIENDSHIP WITH OLIVE.

39:31.456 --> 39:33.893
WE MIGHT NOT LIKE IT,
BUT IT'S THE TRUTH.

39:38.245 --> 39:40.900
WELL,
I'M GONNA NEED A PIE.

39:40.943 --> 39:43.903
Olive: OHH! I'M A SUCKER
FOR SHOOFLY!

39:43.946 --> 39:45.165
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

39:45.208 --> 39:47.559
ARE WE GONNA BE ABLE
TO FIX THIS?

39:47.602 --> 39:48.821
WE SHOULD ASSESS.

39:48.864 --> 39:50.388
I'M WORKING ON

39:50.431 --> 39:52.694
THE "HAVING FEELINGS
FOR YOUR BOYFRIEND" THING.

39:52.738 --> 39:56.350
OH, I JUST WISH THERE WAS
A SWITCH I COULD TURN TO "OFF."

39:56.394 --> 39:57.699
OH, BUT THERE JUST ISN'T.
I KNOW.

39:57.743 --> 39:59.527
AND WHILE YOU DO THAT,

39:59.571 --> 40:01.529
I'M GONNA WORK ON THE
"CENTER OF THE UNIVERSE" THING.

40:01.573 --> 40:03.792
IN FACT, I'M READY TO DITCH
THAT ROLE FOR A NEW ONE --

40:03.836 --> 40:06.665
SELFLESSLY CENTERED
ROOMMATE.

40:06.708 --> 40:08.362
YOU'RE STAYING?

40:08.406 --> 40:09.842
IS THAT A GOOD
OR INCREDULOUS QUESTION MARK

40:09.885 --> 40:10.712
AT THE END
OF THAT QUESTION?

40:10.756 --> 40:12.279
OH, VERY GOOD.

40:12.322 --> 40:16.152
BESIDES, THE HEAVY LIFTING
IS BEHIND US.

40:16.196 --> 40:17.893
WE'VE LAID
THAT CORNERSTONE OF TRUTH.

40:17.937 --> 40:19.460
POUNDED THAT SUCKER
INTO PLACE.

40:19.504 --> 40:20.679
BESIDES,
IT'D BE SUCH A WASTE

40:20.722 --> 40:22.376
OF TIME AND EFFORT
IF YOU LEFT.

40:22.420 --> 40:23.899
AGREED.

40:26.119 --> 40:28.774
Narrator: AS CHUCK AND OLIVE
CELEBRATED THEIR REUNION...

40:28.817 --> 40:30.471
[ FINGERS SNAP, BOTH LAUGH ]

40:30.515 --> 40:33.692
...EMERSON COD
HAD A REUNION OF HIS OWN.

40:33.735 --> 40:35.389
WELL, FINALLY.

40:35.433 --> 40:36.129
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

40:36.172 --> 40:39.437
A DECENT STOGIE.

40:39.480 --> 40:41.221
I NEEDED
SOME COMFORT TOBACCO.

40:41.264 --> 40:42.875
YEAH, I WAS
JUST ABOUT TO RING YOU UP,

40:42.918 --> 40:45.878
TELL YOU HOW MUCH
I REGRETTED OUR PREVIOUS WORDS.

40:45.921 --> 40:48.315
I WAS ABOUT TO GET ON A PLANE,
AND THAT SAME REGRET

40:48.358 --> 40:51.623
HAD ME TURNING AROUND,
RUNNING BACK HERE.

40:51.666 --> 40:55.409
YOU WERE RIGHT.
OUR RELATIONSHIP IS DONE.

40:55.453 --> 40:58.456
MEANING HOW
OUR RELATIONSHIP WAS,

40:58.499 --> 41:00.980
BEING BEST FRIENDS.

41:01.023 --> 41:02.590
I'M YOUR MAMA, EMMY,

41:02.634 --> 41:04.853
AND I GOT TO START
ACTING LIKE IT.

41:04.897 --> 41:06.507
THAT MEANS
I CAN'T EXPECT YOU

41:06.551 --> 41:09.467
TO BE AS STRONG AS ME
OR AS GROWN-UP.

41:11.164 --> 41:14.515
GOT TO FEEL YOU CAN BE
VULNERABLE, MAKE MISTAKES,

41:14.559 --> 41:17.039
AND STILL TELL ME
ABOUT THEM.

41:17.083 --> 41:17.692
DEAL?

41:17.736 --> 41:18.998
YEAH.

41:20.739 --> 41:23.089
DO I GET AN ALLOWANCE?
NO.

41:23.132 --> 41:25.483
BUT YOU DO GET NOTES

41:25.526 --> 41:27.180
ON THIS FROM ME.

41:27.223 --> 41:28.486
[ SIGHS ]

41:28.529 --> 41:29.922
THE PUBLISHER'S RIGHT.

41:29.965 --> 41:32.664
THAT BOOK IS STUPID.

41:32.707 --> 41:36.363
BOOK AIN'T STUPID.
STORY IS.

41:36.406 --> 41:40.323
THIS IS ABOUT YOUR CHILDHOOD
WITH YOUR CRAZY MOTHER.

41:40.367 --> 41:41.542
YOU TELL THAT
TO A KID AT BEDTIME,

41:41.586 --> 41:43.544
HE'LL PISS THE BOX SPRINGS.

41:43.588 --> 41:46.504
YOU GOT TO WRITE ABOUT
THE GROWN-UP EMERSON COD,

41:46.547 --> 41:48.157
HOW GREAT
HE'D BE AS A DADDY.

41:48.201 --> 41:49.898
DO THAT,
AND YOUR LITTLE GIRL

41:49.942 --> 41:51.900
WILL COME RUNNING BACK
IN NO TIME.

41:53.511 --> 41:55.556
[ SMOOCHES ]

41:55.600 --> 41:57.689
[ CHUCKLES ]
LATER, LIL' GUM SHOE.

41:57.732 --> 42:01.214
Narrator: AS EMERSON COD ENJOYED
A SENSE OF FAMILIAL PEACE,

42:01.257 --> 42:04.304
THE PIE MAKER HAD A PEACE
OF A DIFFERENT SORT --

42:04.347 --> 42:07.655
THE QUIET, SOLITARY,
BACHELOR KIND...

42:07.699 --> 42:09.048
UNTIL...
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

42:12.660 --> 42:14.488
OH, NO.
DISASTER WITH OLIVE?

42:14.532 --> 42:17.752
IT WENT REALLY WELL --
SO WELL, IN FACT,

42:17.796 --> 42:19.014
I WANTED TO WRAP YOU
IN GOOSE-DOWN GOODNESS

42:19.058 --> 42:20.450
AS A THANK-YOU.

42:20.494 --> 42:23.628
BUT, YOU KNOW,
MY DUVET WAS METAPHORICAL.

42:23.671 --> 42:26.239
YEAH?
WELL, SO WAS MINE.

42:28.241 --> 42:30.199
OHH.

42:30.243 --> 42:31.853
I'VE REALLY MISSED YOU.
